1. e4 {GM Davorin Kuljasevic} c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. c4 Nc6 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 Nf6 {Last month, I only discussed setups in which Black's knight comes to f6 immediately.} 6. Nc3 Nxd4 (6... d6 7. f3) 7. Qxd4 {GM Davorin Kuljasevic: '?!' GM Davorin Kuljasevic: 'This prophylactic move is wrong here.'} d6 $1 {GM Davorin Kuljasevic: 'without the knight on f6, this move is now strong, preparing ...e7-e5. White does not have a good way of stopping it.'} 8. Be3 (8. c5) (8. e5) 8... Bg7 9. f3 O-O {GM Davorin Kuljasevic: '=' GM Davorin Kuljasevic: 'Black has equalized comfortably out of the opening.'} 10. Qd2 Be6 (10... a5 11. b3 a4 12. b4) 11. Rc1 $4 {Inexplicable blunder from the Armenian number one. Inexplicable blunder from the Armenian number one. GM Davorin Kuljasevic: '?' GM Davorin Kuljasevic: 'A speculative sacrifice that did not work out.'} Qa5 $19 {The rest needs no comment.} 12. b3 (12. Nd5 $11 Qxa2 (12... Qxd2+ 13. Kxd2 Bxd5 (13... Nxd5 14. cxd5 Bd7 15. Rc7) 14. cxd5) 13. Nxe7+ Kh8 14. Bd4 (14. Be2 Ng8) 14... Rfe8 15. Qc3 (15. Nd5 Bxd5 16. cxd5 Rac8) 15... Nh5 16. Bxg7+ (16. g4 Rxe7 17. gxh5 Bxd4 18. Qxd4+ Kg8 19. h6 Qa5+ 20. Kf2 Qe5) 16... Nxg7) 12... Rfc8 (12... a6 13. Be2) 13. Be2 a6 14. Na4 (14. Nd5 Qxd2+ 15. Kxd2 Nxd5 16. cxd5 Bd7 17. Rxc8+ Rxc8 18. Rc1 Rxc1 19. Kxc1 Kf8 20. Kd2 e6 21. Bd3 exd5 22. exd5 Ke7 23. g3 Be5 24. Bg5+ Bf6 25. Be3 $11 {1-0 (30) Van Foreest,L (2499)-Janik,I (2453) Porto Carras 2018} Be5 26. Bg5+ Bf6 {GM Davorin Kuljasevic} 27. Be3 {typical structure with gxf5 (Dominguez-Mamedyarov)} Be5) 14... Qxd2+ 15. Kxd2 Nd7 16. g4 Rcb8 (16... f5 $11 {is unproblematic. 1-0 (85) Van Foreest,L (2481)-Tari,A (2599) Wijk aan Zee 2018}) (16... Rc6 {is probably best. One game saw Black neutralise White's play.}) 17. Nc3 b5 {GM Davorin Kuljasevic: '-+'} 18. Nd5 (18. cxb5 $17 axb5 19. Bxb5 {leads to normal play of course.} (19. Nxb5 Rxa2+ 20. Rc2 Rxc2+ 21. Kxc2 Rc8+) 19... Bxc3+) 18... Bxd5 19. cxd5 (19. exd5 b4) 19... Nc5 (19... Rc8 $15 20. Rc6 {(GM Davorin Kuljasevic) [#]} Ne5 $1 21. Rxc8+ Rxc8 $15 22. Rc1 {GM Davorin Kuljasevic} Rxc1 23. Kxc1) 20. g5 (20. b4 Na4 21. Rc7 a5 $5 {What a mess!} 22. bxa5 $5 (22. Rb1 $1 {All Black needs to focus on is coordination over material. Thus} axb4 23. Rxb4 Nc5 {and White must go for a draw with} 24. Bxc5 dxc5 25. Rxc5 Bh6+ 26. Ke1 Rxa2 27. Rcxb5 Rxb5 {with a typical engine finish.} 28. Rxb5 $5 Bf4) 22... Rxa5 $1 23. Rxe7 $1 {A ridiculous engine line, but there is some logic to the whole thing.} Nc3) (20. Bxc5 $5 dxc5 21. Rxc5 Rc8 (21... Bh6+ 22. Kd3 $44 {[%csl Ga5,Ga7]} Bf4 23. Kd4 (23. h4 Rc8 24. b4 e6 25. dxe6 fxe6 26. h5 Rd8+ 27. Kc3 $15 Rd2) 23... Rc8 24. b4 {is a sound Reti for White.} f6 $2) (21... Be5 22. Ke3 Rc8) 22. Rxc8+ (22. Rc6 $4 Rxc6 23. dxc6 Rc8 $18) 22... Rxc8 23. f4 e5 $13 24. dxe6 fxe6 25. g5 Bc3+ $8 26. Kd3 Bb2 $11 27. Bg4 $2 Kf7 $1 28. Rf1 Rc1 $16 29. Rf2 Rc3+ {mates.} 30. Kd2 a5 {mates.} {Not} 31. f5 exf5 32. exf5 a4 $1 $19 33. f6 (33. Bd1 Rc5 34. bxa4 $6 bxa4 35. fxg6+ Kxg6 $1 36. h4 Rc4 37. Kd3 Rd4+ 38. Kc2 Rb4 $15) 33... Rc5 {White is down a piece but Black's pieces totally lack coordination.} 34. h4 axb3 35. axb3 h6 $17 36. gxh6 Bc1+ $15 37. Kd3 Bxh6 $16) 20... Bb2 21. Rc2 (21. Rb1 Ba3 22. b4 Na4 23. Rb3 Bb2 $36 24. Rb1 Bg7 25. Rc1 Rc8) 21... Ba3 22. Rb1 a5 23. Kd1 Na6 24. Bf1 Nb4 25. Rd2 (25. Rc7 Rc8 26. Rxe7 Nxa2) 25... Rb7 26. f4 Na6 27. Rc2 (27. h4 {is possible but unnecessarily risky. For instance is possible but unnecessarily risky. For instance GM Davorin Kuljasevic: '='} Bc5) 27... Nb4 28. Rd2 Na6 29. Rc2 Nb4 30. Rd2 {and Black may as well transpose to the above note.} 0-1


