1. Nf3 d5 2. c4 e6 3. b3 c5 4. Bb2 Nc6 5. e3 Nf6 6. cxd5 exd5 7. Bb5 Be7 8. O-O O-O 9. d4 Bg4 10. dxc5 Bxc5 11. Bxc6 $5 bxc6 12. Qc2 Bd6 13. Nbd2 ({The greedy} 13. Qxc6 $6 Bxf3 14. gxf3 Re8 {followed by ...e6 is too dangerous for White.}) 13... Rc8 (13... c5 {is probably better} 14. Qd3 {and White has a slightly better position.} (14. Ng5 d4 $1 $13)) 14. Ng5 $1 {Shows the venom in the white setup. xf6 and mate on h7 is threatened.} g6 (14... Qd7 15. Bxf6 Bf5 16. e4 $1 gxf6 17. Nxf7 Bxe4 18. Nxe4 Rxf7 19. Nxd6 Qxd6 20. Rac1 $14 {White has a long-term advantage based on his better structure.} Re7 21. g3 c5 22. Rfd1 Re5 23. Qc3 Qe6 24. Qa5 Qb6 25. Qa4 Rc7 26. Qg4+ Rg5 27. Qf3 Qe6 28. Rd4 Kg7 29. Kg2 Re5 30. Rg4+ Rg5 31. Qf4 Qe7 32. Re1 Qxe1 33. Qxc7+ Kg6 34. Rh4 Rh5 35. Rxh5 Qe4+ 36. f3 Qc2+ 37. Kh3 Kxh5 38. Qg7 Qg6 39. Qxa7 Kh6 40. Qxc5 Qf5+ 41. Kg2 Qd3 42. Qc1+ Kg6 43. Kf2 h5 44. Qb2 d4 45. Qc1 Kg7 46. b4 Kg6 47. a4 Qb3 48. Qd2 Qxa4 49. Qxd4 Qc2+ 50. Kg1 Qb1+ 51. Kg2 Qc2+ 52. Qf2 Qb3 53. Qe2 Kg7 54. b5 Kg6 55. Qe8+ Kh6 56. Qc6 Kg7 57. b6 Kg6 58. b7 Qa2+ 59. Kh3 {1-0 (59) Stripunsky,A (2569)-Smith,B (2384) Philadelphia 2006}) 15. Qc3 $1 Be7 16. h3 Be6 (16... Bd7 {allows} 17. Nde4 $1 dxe4 18. Nxe4 $16 {Black can not prevent xf6+, when White emerges a clear pawn up.}) 17. Rfd1 (17. e4 $1 $16 {was hard to meet.} h6 18. Nxe6 fxe6 19. Qe3 Kh7 20. Qxa7 {and the queen grabbed a pawn.}) 17... c5 18. Qe5 $6 (18. Nde4 $1 h6 $1 19. Nxf6+ (19. Qxf6 $5 Bxf6 20. Nxf6+ Kh8 $2 (20... Qxf6) 21. Nxd5+ Kg8 22. Nxe6 fxe6 23. Nf6+ Qxf6 24. Bxf6 Rxf6 25. Rac1) 19... Bxf6 20. Qxf6 Qxf6 21. Bxf6 hxg5 $14 {and the different coloured bishops give Black good defensive chances.}) 18... Qc7 $11 19. Qc3 {Admits the failure. From an opening perspective the rest of the game is not so interesting.} d4 20. Qd3 Bf5 21. e4 Bd7 22. Re1 Nh5 23. Ngf3 Nf4 24. Qf1 Bc6 25. Nc4 Bf6 26. g3 Ne6 27. Nfd2 Rfe8 28. f4 Bg7 29. e5 Red8 30. Ne4 Bxe4 31. Rxe4 Qc6 32. Qd3 Nc7 33. Nd6 Rb8 34. Rc1 Nb5 35. Nxb5 Qxb5 36. Qxb5 Rxb5 37. Kf1 a5 38. Rc4 Rb4 39. Ba3 Rxc4 40. bxc4 Bf8 41. Ke2 Rb8 42. Kd2 Rb1 43. Re1 Rxe1 44. Kxe1 f6 45. exf6 Kf7 46. Ke2 Kxf6 47. Kf3 g5 48. Bc1 gxf4 49. Bxf4 a4 50. Ke4 Ke6 51. g4 Be7 52. Bh6 Bd6 53. h4 Be7 54. h5 Bd6 55. Bd2 Bf8 56. g5 Be7 57. Kf4 Bf8 58. Kg4 Bd6 59. h6 Kf7 60. Kf5 Bf8 61. Bf4 Be7 62. Be5 Bf8 63. Bf4 Be7 64. Bd2 1/2-1/2


