1. e4 c5 2. c3 d5 3. exd5 Nf6 4. Qa4+ Nbd7 $5 {This is clearly the move I would prefer to play myself although it involves more risk than the alternative ...d7.} 5. c4 e6 ({The crazy-looking} 5... b5 $5 {is actually not out of the question either. Clearly when sacrificing no fewer than two pawns in five moves there's a lot at stake but Black also receives a lot of activity.} {There might follow} 6. Qxb5 Rb8 7. Qa4 e6 ({The rook lift} 7... Rb6 {intending ...e6 next is also interesting.}) 8. dxe6 fxe6 {This opens up the f-file.} ({However keeping the structure by playing} 8... Qe7 {also deserves attention.}) 9. Nf3 Bd6 10. Be2 O-O 11. d3 Bb7 12. Qc2 $6 {This passive move looks a bit too slow and clearly gives Black a dangerous initiative.} (12. Nc3 {looks better develpoing another piece.}) 12... Ne5 $1 {White is already in great danger.} 13. Nbd2 Nfg4 14. h3 {This invites a nice combination but it's already hard to make good suggestions for White.} Nxf2 $1 15. Kxf2 $4 {This automatic reply loses on the spot. He had to play} (15. Rf1 $1 {although Black is better following} Bxf3 16. Nxf3 Rxf3 $1 {Another nice blow!} 17. Bxf3 (17. gxf3 Nxh3 $15 {leaves White's king wide open.}) 17... Nexd3+ 18. Ke2 Be5 $1 19. Rxf2 Nxc1+ 20. Kf1 Rxb2 21. Qxc1 Rxf2+ 22. Kxf2 Qd4+ 23. Ke2 Qxa1 24. Qxa1 Bxa1 $15 {Although Black is symbolically better White now holds an easy draw due to the opposite coloured bishops.}) 15... Qh4+ 16. Kf1 Ng4 $1 17. hxg4 Qxh1+ 18. Kf2 Qh4+ 19. Kf1 Bg3 {0-1 (19) Pedersen,D (2254)-Jaksland,T (2277) Denmark 2014}) 6. dxe6 fxe6 ({Another interesting option is} 6... Qe7 $5 7. Be2 Qxe6 8. Nf3 Bd6 9. Nc3 O-O 10. d4 cxd4 11. Nxd4 Qe5 12. Be3 Nc5 13. Qc2 Ng4 14. Qd2 Nxe3 15. Qxe3 Re8 16. Qxe5 Bxe5 17. O-O-O Ne6 {½-½ (17) Muzik,M (2270)-Civin,T (2270) Czechia 1999}) 7. Nc3 Bd6 8. d3 O-O 9. h3 {A solid move but also a bit time-consuming.} Ne5 10. Be3 Bd7 11. Qc2 Bc6 $6 ({Here I suggest the improvement} 11... Nc6 $146 {when there might follow} 12. Nf3 e5 13. Be2 Nd4 {intending ...c6 next. Black has full compensation for the sacrificed pawn due to his piece activity and central control.}) 12. Nge2 a6 13. Rg1 b5 14. f4 Ng6 15. g3 Qb6 16. Ne4 Be7 17. N2c3 Nxe4 18. dxe4 Rad8 19. Bd3 b4 20. Nd1 a5 21. Nf2 a4 22. Rd1 Qb7 23. Qe2 Rf7 24. h4 Nf8 25. Kf1 Nd7 26. Bb1 Rdf8 27. Ke1 b3 28. a3 Bd8 29. Bd2 Bf6 30. Be3 Bd8 31. Rd6 e5 32. f5 Ba5+ 33. Kf1 Qc7 34. Rd1 Qb7 35. g4 g6 36. h5 Re8 37. hxg6 hxg6 38. Rd6 Rf6 39. Rd1 Rf7 40. Qf3 Nf8 41. Qg3 Rd7 42. Rxd7 Qxd7 43. Ke2 Qf7 44. Rh1 Bb7 45. Bd3 Nh7 46. Rh6 1-0


