1. e4 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K''} c5 2. c3 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'David Howell was a very tough opponent to prepare against - he played many different openings and somehow I wasn't expecting 1.e4 and definitely not the Alapin Variation, that he had played a lot in the past. After this small surprise, I chose to play an old line I trusted. Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: 'David Howell was a very tough opponent to prepare against - he played many different openings and somehow I wasn't expecting 1.e4 and definitely not the Alapin Variation, that he had played a lot in the past. After this small surprise, I chose to play an old line I trusted.'''} Nf6 3. e5 Nd5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Bc4 Nb6 6. Bb3 c4 7. Bc2 d5 ({I had bad experiences in the past in this main line, judging it to be too dangerous after for example:} 7... Qc7 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K'} 8. O-O $5 Nxe5 9. Nxe5 Qxe5 10. Re1 Qc7 11. a4 $1 d5 12. Na3 a6 13. a5 Nd7 14. d3 $44 {1-0 (44) Jones,G (2667)-Rowson,J (2565) London 2016, with a very strong initiative and compensation for the sacrificed pawn.}) 8. exd6 e5 9. O-O Be6 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'The idea is to wait for White to define whether he is taking with the queen or with the bishop on d3 (after the move d4). On the other hand, I remembered that White had some strong move on the queenside that could give me problems, and also that I had to be watching the annoying ...g5 all the time. Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: 'The idea is to wait for White to define whether he is taking with the queen or with the bishop on d3 (after the move d4). On the other hand, I remembered that White had some strong move on the queenside that could give me problems, and also that I had to be watching the annoying ...g5 all the time.'''} (9... Bxd6 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K' is a fine move, but I had an impression that White obtains an initiative somehow} 10. d3 cxd3 11. Qxd3 Be6 {this is similar to White's 10th move analysis} 12. Rd1 (12. Re1 {-- 10.e1}) (12. Bb3 Qe7 13. Re1 Bxb3 14. axb3 O-O {followed by ...f5, lack is doing fine} 15. Na3 f5 (15... Bxa3 $5 16. bxa3 f5 $36) 16. Nc4 Nxc4 17. Qxc4+ Kh8 18. Bg5 Qf7 (18... Qc7 $11) 19. Qxf7 Rxf7 20. b4 e4 $11 {with a balanced endgame: ½-½ (41) Adams,M (2740)-Wojtaszek,R (2733) Biel 2015}) 12... Be7 13. Qe2 Qc7 14. a4 O-O 15. Ng5 (15. a5 Nc4 16. a6 Rfd8 17. axb7 Rxd1+ 18. Bxd1 Qxb7 $11) 15... Bxg5 16. Bxg5 f5 17. a5 Nd5 18. a6 h6 19. Bc1 b6 $13 {1-0 (63) Gara,A (2354)-Muzychuk,A (2587) Riga 2017, with an unbalanced position, Black has potential in the centre, but has to watch White's bishop pair.}) 10. a4 $5 {Recommended by Dave Smerdon in his notes to M. Adams - R.Wojtaszek, Biel 2015 (1/2 - 1/2 in 41). Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '!' '!' '!' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: '!?' '!?' Sam Collins: 'Recommended by Dave Smerdon in his notes to M. Adams - R.Wojtaszek, Biel 2015 (1/2 - 1/2 in 41).' Sam Collins: 'Recommended by Dave Smerdon in his notes to M. Adams - R.Wojtaszek, Biel 2015 (1/2 - 1/2 in 41). Mekhitarian,K: '!''' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'There it is! Found over the board by my opponent, after a long think. This typical Alapin move threatening a5 is usually a problem, because if Black plays ...a5 avoiding it, then the knight becomes loose and b5 could be a juicy square for that b1-knight. Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: 'There it is! Found over the board by my opponent, after a long think. This typical Alapin move threatening a5 is usually a problem, because if Black plays ...a5 avoiding it, then the knight becomes loose and b5 could be a juicy square for that b1-knight.'''} (10. Re1 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K'} Bxd6 11. d4 cxd3 12. Qxd3 {Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: '-- 10.e1''} h6 {followed by ...c7, trying to exchange queens, Black is fine. The advantage I remembered from my old preparation, is that White had already chosen e1 (and I thought d1 was an annoying move).}) (10. d4 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K'} cxd3 11. Bxd3 (11. Qxd3 Qxd6 {trying to exchange queens - the endgame is fine for Black with this strong pawn on e5} 12. Qxd6 Bxd6 13. Nbd2 f6 14. b3 O-O-O 15. Bb2 Be7 $15 {0-1 (51) Potapov,P (2497)-Kovalev,V (2629) Minsk 2017}) 11... Qxd6 12. Qc2 (12. Ng5 Bd5 $11 {followed by ...d8}) 12... Rd8 13. Be4 Bd5 14. Re1 Bxe4 15. Qxe4 f6 16. Nbd2 g6 17. Nc4 Nxc4 18. Qxc4 Qd5 19. Qxd5 Rxd5 20. Be3 Kf7 $15 {0-1 (63) Pavasovic,D (2568)-Fier,A (2588) Khanty-Mansiysk 2010, and Black is doing fine again.}) 10... Bxd6 {Dave covered 10... Qxd6 and 10...a5. Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Dave covered 10... Qxd6 and 10...a5.''} (10... a6 {looks logical, preventing White's pawn from reaching a6, but White can open the position to his advantage after Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'looks logical, preventing White's pawn from reaching a6, but White can open the position to his advantage after''} 11. a5 Nd7 12. d4 cxd3 13. Qxd3 Nc5 14. Qe2 Bxd6 {P.Roberson - A.Bitalzadeh, chess.com INT 2017 (0-1 in 52) and now Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'P.Roberson - A.Bitalzadeh, chess.com INT 2017 (0-1 in 52) and now'' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'White has a dangerous initiative on the kingside with g5 right now, or even moves like bd2 followed by c4. Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: 'White has a dangerous initiative on the kingside with g5 right now, or even moves like bd2 followed by c4.'''} 15. Nbd2 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '!?' '!?' '!?' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: '!?'''} (15. Rd1 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K'} Qc7 (15... Nb3 $1 $13 {was very good to complicate matters}) 16. b4 $2 (16. Nbd2 $1 $16 {and c4}) 16... Nb3 17. Bxb3 Bxb3 18. Re1 O-O $11 {0-1 (52) Roberson,P (2397)-Bitalzadeh,A (2383) chess.com INT 2017}) (15. Ng5 $5 $16 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K' looks very strong}) 15... h6 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins'} 16. Nc4 $16 {is excellent for White.}) (10... Qxd6 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K'} 11. Ng5 $1 Bd5 12. a5 Nd7 13. d3 cxd3 14. Qxd3 $14) (10... a5 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K'} 11. b3 $1 {is very problematic for Black} (11. Na3 $5 Bxd6 12. Nb5 Bb8 13. d4 cxd3 14. Bxd3 h6 15. Re1 O-O 16. Qc2 $14) 11... Bxd6 12. bxc4 Bxc4 13. Re1 O-O 14. Na3 Bd5 15. Nb5 Bb8 16. d3 Re8 17. Rb1 $16) 11. a5 Nd7 12. d4 (12. a6 $5 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins'} bxa6 {seems to be a useful inclusion:} 13. Be4 (13. Rxa6 Qc8 $11 {1/2-1/2 (38) Roberson,P (2401)-Lalic,B (2443) London 2016}) (13. d4 $5) 13... Rc8 14. d4 exd4 15. Bxc6 Rxc6 16. Nxd4 Rb6 17. Nxe6 fxe6 18. Qh5+ g6 19. Qh3 $16) 12... cxd3 13. Qxd3 Be7 14. a6 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '!' '!' '!' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: '!''' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'My knight on c6 will feel very loose without the b7-pawn. Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: 'My knight on c6 will feel very loose without the b7-pawn.'''} b6 (14... bxa6 15. Qxa6 $16 {is also excellent for White. Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: '' '' Sam Collins: 'is also excellent for White.''} Rc8 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K'} 16. Rd1 O-O 17. Be3 Qc7 18. Na3 $16 {looks very good for White also.}) 15. Re1 $6 {According to the engines this gives up some of White's advantage, but I find this assessment hard to believe. Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'According to the engines this gives up some of White's advantage, but I find this assessment hard to believe.''} (15. Rd1 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins'} Rc8 16. Na3 f5 17. Nb5 O-O 18. Qe2 $16 {was H.Stevic - B.Lalic, Mali Losinj 2017  (1-0 in 48).}) (15. Na3 $1 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K' was more important right away, e1 is not necessarily good, since the e-pawn is safe} Bxa3 16. Rxa3 h6 {avoiding g5} 17. Nd2 $1 $16 {with strong c4 and e4 threats - meanwhile Black is still not able to castle.}) 15... Rc8 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '!' '!' '!' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: '!''' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Defending the loose knight on c6 is a very good idea. Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: 'Defending the loose knight on c6 is a very good idea.'''} 16. Na3 Bxa3 17. Rxa3 f6 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '?' '?' '?' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: '?'''} (17... h6 {is the move the engines want to play, though it's hard to see how Black will bring his king to safety. To me this position just looks horrible for Black even though Stockfish says its just a white edge. Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '' '' '' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'is the move the engines want to play, though it's hard to see how Black will bring his king to safety. To me this position just looks horrible for Black even though Stockfish says its just a white edge.' Sam Collins: 'is the move the engines want to play, though it's hard to see how Black will bring his king to safety. To me this position just looks horrible for Black even though Stockfish says its just a white edge. Mekhitarian,K: '''' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'was necessary to avoid g5 and at the same time, keep the e6-bishop safe. I didn't want to play this because now ...f6-f7 is no longer an option. Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: 'was necessary to avoid g5 and at the same time, keep the e6-bishop safe. I didn't want to play this because now ...f6-f7 is no longer an option.'''} 18. Ra1 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K'} Qc7 $5 {threatening ...b4 and also ...c5 followed by castling.}) 18. Be3 $6 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '?' '?' '?' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: '?!' '?!' Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: '?''' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Now Black suddenly is fine, my opponent underestimated the idea of playing ...f7 and keeping it safe. Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: 'Now Black suddenly is fine, my opponent underestimated the idea of playing ...f7 and keeping it safe.'''} (18. Nd4 $1 $16 {was an important opportunity. If Black takes on d4 the a3-rook can come into play along the third rank, and after Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '!' '!' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'was critical'} Nc5 19. Qg3 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '!' '!'} exd4 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'is the move that kept my opponent thinking for a long time'} (19... Kf7 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K' is just horrible for Black (during the game, I thought this was somehow playable)} 20. Nxe6 Nxe6 21. Bb3 $18 {followed by f4}) 20. Qxg7 Rf8 21. b4 $16 {the complications favour White. Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '!' '!'} (21. Bh6 $2 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K' is not impressive} Rf7 $1 22. Qg8+ Ke7 $19) (21. Bxh7 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K'} Qe7 $1 $15 {and Black survives}) 21... Rc7 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K'} 22. Qh6 {if I give up the piece by playing ...e7, then I'm simply worse. And ...d3 doesn't work either:} d3 23. Bd1 $1 $18 {[%csl Rc5,Re6]} (23. bxc5 $6 dxc2 24. Rxe6+ Re7 25. Rxe7+ Nxe7 26. Qd2 $14)) 18... Kf7 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '!' '!' '!' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: '!'''} (18... Qc7 {followed by ...Ne7 was a better defence. Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '(Sam Collins) followed by ...Ne7 was a better defence.'}) 19. Raa1 (19. Nh4 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K'} g6 $1 20. Nxg6 $2 hxg6 21. Qxg6+ Ke7 $19 {and ...f7.}) 19... Qc7 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Threatening ...b4, something that my opponent missed having only 1 minute on the clock to make 20 moves before time control (I had around 40). Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: 'Threatening ...b4, something that my opponent missed having only 1 minute on the clock to make 20 moves before time control (I had around 40).'''} 20. Rad1 $2 {Allowing an equalising shot. Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Allowing an equalising shot.''} (20. Qe2 $14 {would retain an excellent position. Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: '' '' Sam Collins: 'would retain an excellent position.''} Nb4 $1 $11 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K' followed by ...d5.}) 20... Nb4 $1 21. Qe2 (21. cxb4 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins'} Qxc2 $15 {is no improvement.}) 21... Nxc2 22. Qxc2 Nb8 $11 {Important attacking pieces have been exchanged and White needs to concern himself with defence of his a6-pawn. The game was drawn after further adventures. Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: '=' '=' Sam Collins: 'Important attacking pieces have been exchanged and White needs to concern himself with defence of his a6-pawn. The game was drawn after further adventures.''} 23. Qa4 Rhd8 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '' '' '' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: ''''} 24. h3 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'It is not clear how to improve now. My position is definitely better - my pieces are well placed, his a6-pawn is weak, and most importantly, his minor pieces are badly placed hitting my solid structure (f3-knight and e3-bishop). Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: 'It is not clear how to improve now. My position is definitely better - my pieces are well placed, his a6-pawn is weak, and most importantly, his minor pieces are badly placed hitting my solid structure (f3-knight and e3-bishop).'''} Qc4 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '!' '!' '!' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: '!'''} (24... Bd5 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K' I thought about this, but didn't see how to proceed after} 25. Nd2 $15) 25. Qa3 Qb3 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Exchanging queens is good to make the a6-pawn even weaker. Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: 'Exchanging queens is good to make the a6-pawn even weaker.'''} 26. Qxb3 Bxb3 27. Rxd8 Rxd8 28. Nd2 Be6 29. Ra1 Bc8 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '?!' '?!' '?!' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: '?!'''} (29... Nc6 $1 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K' avoiding xb6 and trying to expand my kingside majority.} 30. f3 f5 $15) 30. b4 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '!' '!' '!' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: '!'''} Bxa6 31. c4 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '!?' '!?' '!?' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: '!?''' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Suddenly White tries to play for some tricks. Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: 'Suddenly White tries to play for some tricks.'''} (31. b5 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K' was already good enough for a draw} Bxb5 32. Rxa7+ Rd7 (32... Kg6 33. Rb7 Nd7 34. Bxb6 $11) 33. Bxb6 $11) 31... Rd7 32. b5 Bc8 33. c5 bxc5 34. Ne4 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'After all the middlegame mess, I was short on time with less than a minute, like my opponent! Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: 'After all the middlegame mess, I was short on time with less than a minute, like my opponent!'''} Rc7 35. Bxc5 Ke6 36. Bxa7 (36. Rxa7 $11 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K' forced the draw right away.}) 36... Nd7 37. g4 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '?!' '?!' '?!' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: '?!''' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'This was unnecessary chances. Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: 'This was unnecessary chances.'''} Bb7 38. Ng3 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '?!' '?!' '?!' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: '?!'''} (38. Nd2 $1 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K' followed by e3, setting up a fortress, and also avoiding ideas like d3-b3, that could try to win the b5-pawn.}) 38... g6 (38... Rc3 $1 $17 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K' followed by ...b3 and after winning the b5-pawn, I have chances to push for a win - the opposite coloured bishops sometimes is good to create attacking patterns, when there are more pieces.}) 39. Re1 {Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: '' '' '' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: '''' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Here my opponent offered a draw - we both had 30 seconds, but there was a 30-minute bonus coming in the next move (40). I wanted to play ...c2, but for some reason I got scared of e2 (that threatens a fork on d4, but something I can defend in many ways), and besides that, I was happy with the overall result, because I was playing a very tough opponent, and also because I had had very bad position in the opening. Still, my decision to accept the draw was clearly wrong, since I still had something to play for: if I'm able to win the b-pawn, then White may have a hard time defending the endgame, specially after his g4 move. Naturally, he has huge drawing chances, but there was no risk at all for me. Anyway, a very rich game full of ideas!' Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag: 'Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K: 'Here my opponent offered a draw - we both had 30 seconds, but there was a 30-minute bonus coming in the next move (40). I wanted to play ...c2, but for some reason I got scared of e2 (that threatens a fork on d4, but something I can defend in many ways), and besides that, I was happy with the overall result, because I was playing a very tough opponent, and also because I had had very bad position in the opening. Still, my decision to accept the draw was clearly wrong, since I still had something to play for: if I'm able to win the b-pawn, then White may have a hard time defending the endgame, specially after his g4 move. Naturally, he has huge drawing chances, but there was no risk at all for me. Anyway, a very rich game full of ideas!'''} Rc2 $1 {(Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag) Sam Collins: 'Mekhitarian,K'} 40. Ne2 Kf7 41. Rd1 Ke7 42. Re1 Rb2 $17 1/2-1/2


