1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. c3 Nf6 4. e5 Nd5 5. d4 cxd4 6. cxd4 d6 7. Bc4 Nc6 8. O-O Be7 9. a3 O-O 10. Re1 Qb6 11. exd6 Bxd6 12. Qd3 Bd7 ({Varying from the} 12... Nf6 {of D.Howell (2528) - J.Mestel (2470), 4NCL 2007/08 (1-0 in 31), analysed by Andrew Martin in the Archives.}) 13. Nc3 Nce7 {This seems like the most harmonious development. Black reinforces his blockade on d5 and frees his knight to come to f6. The bishop might come to c6 on a good day.} 14. Ng5 ({White could also start with} 14. Ne4 {. After} Nf4 (14... Ng6 {also looks reasonable}) 15. Bxf4 Bxf4 16. Nfg5 Bxg5 17. Nxg5 Ng6 {Black looks solid, though White can continue as Howell did with} 18. h4 $5) 14... Nf6 15. Nce4 Nxe4 16. Qxe4 {A tough choice.} (16. Nxe4 Rac8 17. Bd2 (17. Nxd6 Qxd6 {is equal}) 17... Bxh2+ 18. Kxh2 Qc7+ 19. g3 Qxc4 20. Qxc4 Rxc4 21. Bb4 Nf5 22. Bxf8 Kxf8 23. Rac1 Rxc1 24. Rxc1 Bc6 {with enough compensation for the sacrificed exchange.}) 16... Ng6 17. h4 $5 {Ambitiously playing for the win.} ({Howell could have bailed out with} 17. d5 exd5 18. Qxd5 Qc7 19. Nxf7 Bxh2+ 20. Kh1 Bc6 {and White should take the draw with} 21. Nh6+ Kh8 22. Nf7+ Kg8 23. Nh6+) 17... Rac8 18. b3 Qa5 19. Be3 b5 (19... Bc6 20. Qg4 Qf5 {also looks like a sound defence.}) 20. b4 Qd8 21. Ba2 {White has succeeded in outplaying his highly-rated opponent and has very active play.} Re8 22. h5 Nf8 23. Rac1 {Allowing Black to relieve the pressure.} (23. Qf3 Qf6 (23... Qe7 24. h6 {is very risky}) 24. Qxf6 gxf6 25. Ne4 Be7 26. d5 exd5 27. Bxd5 {and Black will have to suffer to make a draw.}) 23... h6 $1 {An important move, defending the kingside.} 24. Nf3 Rxc1 25. Rxc1 a5 26. Bf4 Qe7 27. Bxd6 Qxd6 28. Qe5 Qa6 29. Bb1 axb4 30. axb4 {The position is balanced and a draw is a fair result.} Qa3 31. Qe1 e5 32. dxe5 Bg4 33. Be4 Bxh5 34. Bc6 Rd8 35. Ra1 Qb3 36. Rb1 Qe6 37. Rc1 Ng6 38. Qe3 Bxf3 39. Bxf3 Qxe5 40. Qxe5 Nxe5 41. Rc5 Nxf3+ 42. gxf3 Rb8 {An interesting theoretical encounter. I like White in most c3-Sicilian IQPs and the one arising after 12...Bd7 is no different.} 1/2-1/2


