1. d4 {Paunovic,Tomislav} d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. e4 b5 4. a4 c6 5. Nc3 a6 6. axb5 cxb5 7. Nxb5 axb5 8. Rxa8 Bb7 9. Ra1 e6 10. Be2 Nf6 11. Nf3 Nxe4 12. O-O Nc6 13. b3 {Paunovic,Tomislav: 'N' A novelty in this sharp line.} (13. Be3 {(Paunovic,Tomislav) - 121/(118)}) 13... Na5 {Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Diagram '} (13... Nc3 $142 {Paunovic,Tomislav} 14. Qc2 Nxe2+ 15. Qxe2 Nxd4 16. Nxd4 Qxd4 17. Bb2 Qd5 18. f3 Bc5+ 19. Kh1 O-O 20. Rfd1 $1 Qc6 21. bxc4 bxc4 22. Rdc1 $14) 14. Bxc4 $5 {Definitely a surprising move. White is an exchange up but gives the bishop for two pawns. In the arising position Black has two pieces for rook and pawn but the knight on a5 has trouble to come back into the game.} (14. bxc4 {Paunovic,Tomislav} Nc3 15. Bg5 $1 Qb8 (15... f6 $2 16. Qe1 Nxe2+ 17. Qxe2 $18) (15... Be7 16. Bxe7 Qxe7 17. Qc2 Nxe2+ 18. Qxe2 Nxc4 19. Ra7 $16) 16. Qc2 Nxe2+ 17. Qxe2 Nxc4 18. d5 $1 $16) 14... bxc4 15. bxc4 Nc3 $6 {Black sacrificed an exchange in the opening and is still in "fast forward mode". However, his knights find no targets in White's camp and lack coordination. More circumspect was} (15... Be7 16. Qa4+ {Paunovic,Tomislav} Nc6 17. Re1 f5 18. Rb1 $14 {}) ({or} 15... Nc6 {though White in both cases has nothing to complain about.} 16. d5 {Paunovic,Tomislav} Nb8 17. Re1 Nc5 (17... exd5 $6 18. Qb3 $1 Bc5 19. Be3 Bxe3 20. Rxe3 $18) 18. Rb1 $1 Nbd7 19. Nd4 $16 {}) 16. Qd3 (16. Qc2 $5 {Paunovic,Tomislav} Bb4 17. Bd2 Ne2+ (17... Be4 $2 18. Qb2 Ne2+ 19. Kh1 Bxd2 20. Nxd2 $18) 18. Kh1 Bxd2 19. Qxd2 Nb3 20. Qxe2 Nxa1 21. Rxa1 $16) 16... Bb4 (16... Bxf3 $2 17. Qxc3 Be2 18. Re1 $18) 17. d5 {Interrupts the diagonal of the bishop on b7 to have time to exploit the precarious position of the black pieces on the queenside.} Nb3 $6 {This knight attack is more than Black's position can bear.} ({Safer was} 17... Ba6 18. Ne5 {Paunovic,Tomislav} Nxd5 19. Bd2 Bxd2 20. Qxd2 Nxc4 21. Nxc4 Bxc4 22. Rfc1 $16) 18. Ba3 $1 Nc5 (18... Qe7 {Paunovic,Tomislav} 19. Bxb4 Qxb4 20. dxe6 fxe6 21. Rae1 $18) 19. Qe3 Qa5 20. Bb2 N3a4 21. Bxg7 Rg8 22. Bd4 {Paunovic,Tomislav: '+-'} Rg4 (22... Bc3 {Paunovic,Tomislav} 23. Bxc3 Qxc3 24. Qf4) 23. Rfb1 {Emphasizing the bad position of Black's pieces.} Re4 24. Qg5 Rxd4 {Black gives the exchange but that does not really help.} 25. Nxd4 Bc3 26. Qg8+ Ke7 27. Rxb7+ 1-0


