{With Giri fighting to a draw against L'Ami, the chasing pack was ripe for a shake-up, of which British Champion Howell was happy to take part.} 1. e4 {Bjelajac,Milan} e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Bc5 5. Be3 Qf6 6. c3 Nge7 7. Bc4 Ne5 8. Be2 Qg6 9. O-O d6 10. Kh1 O-O 11. Nd2 Ng4 12. Bf4 Nc6 13. f3 Nge5 (13... Nf6 $11 {Bjelajac,Milan}) 14. Be3 $146 {Bjelajac,Milan: 'N!'} ({deviating from} 14. Nxc6 {Mussanti-Popa (2002).}) 14... Bb6 15. f4 Nxd4 16. cxd4 Nc6 17. f5 Qf6 18. e5 {Bjelajac,Milan: '!'} (18. Nf3 {bolstering the d-pawn and garnering threats to ensnare Black's queen may have been a better try.}) 18... dxe5 19. Ne4 Qd8 (19... Qh4 {Bjelajac,Milan} 20. Bd3 $1 $40 h6 $140 21. g3 Qd8 22. Qh5 Nxd4 23. f6 $1) 20. Bc4 {Bjelajac,Milan: '!'} Na5 ({With} 20... exd4 {standing as a viable alternative, the text proves unsavoury.} 21. Qh5 $1 $18 {Bjelajac,Milan} dxe3 $140 22. f6 $1) 21. f6 {Bjelajac,Milan: '+-!'} Bxd4 {was the straw that broke the camel's back. Either of} (21... g6) (21... Nxc4 {were viable.} 22. Qh5 {Bjelajac,Milan}) 22. fxg7 Kxg7 23. Bg5 {With his king's position compromised, and White's heavy artillery lying in wait, Nyback sagely admitted defeat.} 1-0


