{Diagram [#]} 72... Be4 $2 {A serious blunder throwing away the win. But if you don't have enough time on your clock, you tend to play solidly} (72... a1=Q $1 {This is the only winning move} 73. Bxa1 Ka2 74. Bd4 Kb1 $1 75. Be3 b3 76. Kc3 Bc2 $1 $19 {and, after this difficult move it's curtains for White}) 73. Ba1 $1 $11 {Now it's a draw} Bf5 {Diagram [#]} 74. Bd4 $4 {But this move is completely pointless - the bishop does nothing on d4, while on a1 it was blocking the most advanced pawn. It seems that both players missed the a1 idea} (74. Kc1 Kb3 75. Kd2) 74... b3 $4 $11 {but this is just bad, as Black cannot achieve any progress if he doesn't spot the a1 idea} (74... a1=Q 75. Bxa1 Ka2) 75. Kc1 $11 {Now it's a fortress. The players agreed to a draw after a few more moves} Kb4 76. Kd2 Kc4 77. Bb2 Bg6 78. Ke3 Bf5 79. Kd2 Bg6 80. Ke3 Kc5 81. Kd2 Kd5 82. Ke3 Bc2 83. Ba1 Bd1 84. Bb2 Kc4 85. Kd2 Bf3 86. Ba1 Kb4 87. Bb2 Bg4 88. Ba1 Kc4 89. Bb2 Kd5 90. Ke3 Bh3 91. Ba1 Bf1 92. Bb2 Kc4 93. Kd2 1/2-1/2


