1. d4 {Krasenkow,M Krasenkow Krasenkow Krasenkow: 'Krasenkow,Michal Krasenkow,Michal: 'Krasenkow''} Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Bg5 Ne4 5. Bh4 Nxc3 6. bxc3 dxc4 7. e3 Be6 8. Be2 Bg7 9. Nf3 c5 {This rare move deserves serious attention.} (9... O-O {or}) (9... Nd7 {are usually played.}) 10. O-O O-O (10... cxd4 11. Nxd4 Bd5 (11... Bd7 12. Bxc4 Nc6 13. Bd5 O-O 14. Rb1 Qc7 15. Bg3 Qc8 16. Qb3 e6 17. Bf3 e5 18. Nb5 $14 {1-0 Damljanovic,B (2551)-Bok,B (2360)/Arinsal 2009/CBM 131 Extra (45)}) 12. e4 $1 Bc6 (12... Bxe4 13. Bxc4 $44 {[%cal Yf1e1]}) 13. Bxc4 O-O 14. Qb3 Qc7 15. Rfd1 e6 16. Bg3 Qa5 {1/2 Leitao,R (2601)-Lima,D (2466)/Sao Paulo 2006/EXT 2007 (27)} 17. Bd6 Rd8 18. Nxc6 Nxc6 19. Qxb7 $14) 11. Rb1 {This move should not be dangerous.} (11. Qc2 Nc6 12. dxc5 Bf5 13. Qb2 Be4 14. Nd2 Bd3 15. Nxc4 Bxc3 16. Qxc3 Bxe2 17. Rfc1 Qd3 $11 {1/2 Enklaar,B-Robatsch,K (2460)/Amsterdam 1972/MCL (39)}) (11. Qb1 Nc6 12. Qxb7 Bd5 13. Qb5 cxd4 14. Nxd4 Rb8 15. Qc5 Rc8 16. Nxc6 Rxc6 17. Qxa7 Qa8 18. Qxa8 Rxa8 19. Rfd1 e6 20. Rac1 f5 21. Bf3 $1 $11 {1/2 Harikrishna,P (2672)-Howell,D (2606)/Wijk aan Zee 2010/CBM 135 (51)}) (11. Ng5 $5 {is critical:} Bd5 (11... Bf5 $5 12. Bxc4 Nc6 13. Qb3 e6 14. Nf3 Qb6 15. Nd2 cxd4 16. cxd4 Rfc8 $11 {1-0 Harikrishna,P (2673)-Avrukh,B (2645)/Gibraltar 2009/CBM 128 Extra (38)}) 12. e4 Bc6 (12... h6 13. exd5 hxg5 14. Bxg5 cxd4 15. Bxc4 dxc3 (15... Qd6 $6 16. Re1 Re8 17. cxd4 Nd7 18. Rb1 Rac8 19. Qe2 Bf6 20. Bxf6 Nxf6 21. Rxb7 Nxd5 22. Bb3 $16 {1-0 Jianu,V (2533)-Shishkin,V (2498)/Baia Sprie 2009/CBM 130 Extra (43)}) 16. Re1 $1 (16. Rc1 Qd6 (16... Qc7 $5) 17. Re1 Re8 18. Qe2 Kf8 19. Qf3 Nd7 20. Bf4 Qc5 (20... Qb4 $1 $15 {Mikhalchishin}) 21. Bb3 Kg8 $13 {1-0 Harikrishna,P (2659)-Svidler,P (2727)/Dresden 2008/CBM 128/[Ftacnik] (27)}) 16... Qc7 (16... Bf6 17. Bxf6 {1/2 Banikas,H (2582)-Rodshtein,M (2650)/Budva 2009/CBM 130}) 17. Qg4 $5 $36 (17. Qd3 $6 Nd7 18. Bxe7 Rfc8 19. Bb3 Ne5 20. Rxe5 Qxe5 21. d6 c2 22. Rc1 Rc3 23. Qd2 Bf6 $17 {1/2 Vekshenkov,N (2432)-Sherbakov,R (2496)/Belgorod 2008/EXT 2010 (37)})) 13. d5 Bb5 14. a4 Ba6 15. Rc1 (15. Qd2 e6 16. Nf3 Qd6 17. e5 Qxd5 18. Qe3 Nd7 19. Rfd1 Qc6 $15 {1-0 Gligoric,S (2600)-Portisch,L (2630)/Amsterdam 1971/MCL (41)}) (15. Qc2 $5 Qa5 16. Rfc1 Nd7 17. f4 h6 18. Nf3 $44 {1-0 Ivanisevic,I (2542)-Popovic,P (2508)/Herceg Novi 2005/CBM 106 ext (52)}) 15... h6 16. Nh3 b5 17. axb5 Bxb5 18. f4 Nd7 19. Qe1 Nb6 20. f5 $44 {1-0 Langeweg,K (2390)-Roos,D (2350)/Metz 1987/EXT 2004 (37)}) 11... Nd7 $146 {The most principled developing move but Black has some good alternatives.} (11... Qc7 $5 12. Qa4 Bf5 (12... Nd7 $143 13. e4 Nb6 14. Qa3 cxd4 15. Nxd4 Rfe8 16. Bg3 Qd7 17. Nb5 Rec8 18. Rfd1 Qc6 19. Qxe7 $16 {1-0 Rashkovsky,N-Zlotnik,B/Perm 1971/EXT 2001 (53)}) 13. Rbc1 Bd3 14. Bxd3 cxd3 15. Qc4 e6 {1/2 Iljushin,A (2549)-Maslak,K (2510)/Moscow 2008/CBM 122 Extra}) (11... cxd4 12. Nxd4 (12. cxd4 Qd7 13. Ng5 Bd5 14. e4 Bc6 15. Bxc4 Bxd4 16. Qb3 e5 17. Ne6 Bxe4 18. Nxf8 Kxf8 $13 {1/2 Leitao,R (2586)-Lima,D (2529)/Sao Paulo 2005/EXT 2006 (77)}) 12... Bd5 13. Qc2 Qd7 14. e4 Bc6 15. Bxc4 Bxd4 16. cxd4 Qxd4 17. Rbd1 Qxe4 18. Qxe4 Bxe4 19. Rfe1 Bf5 20. Bxe7 Re8 21. f3 Nc6 22. Bf6 Rxe1+ 23. Rxe1 Be6 24. Bxe6 Re8 25. Bxf7+ Kxf7 {1/2 Moiseenko,A (2676)-Kurnosov,I (2602)/Moscow 2009/CBM 129}) (11... b6 $5 12. dxc5 Nd7 13. c6 $6 (13. cxb6 $11) 13... Nf6 14. Nd4 Bd5 15. Bf3 Rc8 16. Bg3 Ne4 17. Nb5 Nxg3 18. hxg3 Bxf3 19. Qxf3 a6 20. c7 Qe8 21. Nd4 e5 22. Nc2 e4 23. Qf4 b5 $17 {1-0 Delchev,A (2625)-Le Roux,J (2512)/France 2010/CBM 135 Extra (55)}) 12. Rxb7 (12. Ng5 {should be checked, e.g.} Bd5 13. e4 h6 (13... cxd4 $6 14. exd5 d3 15. Bf3) 14. exd5 hxg5 15. Bxg5 cxd4 16. d6 $1 Qa5 $1 17. Bxe7 d3 $1 {, apparently with good counterplay for Black.}) 12... cxd4 $6 {A bit premature.} (12... Bd5 $142 13. Rb2 cxd4 $11) 13. cxd4 (13. Nxd4 $1 Bd5 14. Rb4 (14. Rb5 Nb6) 14... Rc8 15. f3 $14 {[%cal Ye3e4]}) 13... Bd5 14. Rb4 $1 Nb6 15. Qb1 Qd6 16. Bg3 Qc6 17. Rc1 Rac8 (17... Be4 $142 18. Qb2 Rfc8 {[%cal Yc4c3]}) 18. a4 (18. Rb5 $1 $14 Be4 $140 19. Qb4) 18... Be4 19. Qa1 c3 20. Ba6 Nd5 $1 21. Bb7 Qf6 $2 {After this move Black loses material without sufficient compensation. It was better to give up the exchange keeping his c-pawn and moving it to c2:} (21... Qd7 $1 22. Rb5 c2 $1 23. Nd2 $1 Bd3 $1 24. Rb3 Bf5 25. Bxc8 Rxc8 $44 {[%cal Yg7h6]} 26. e4 $2 Bh6) 22. Rb5 Rcd8 $6 (22... e6 23. Bxc8 Rxc8 24. Ne5 $16) 23. Ne5 (23. Bh4 $1 {[%cal Yf3g5] was even stronger, e.g.} Qe6 (23... Qf5 24. Bxe7) 24. Ng5 Qg4 25. Nxe4 Qxe4 26. Bxe7 Qxe7 27. Bxd5 $18) 23... a6 24. Rc5 Qb6 25. Bxd5 Bxd5 26. Qxc3 Bxe5 27. Bxe5 {With a pawn up and a superior position, White slowly but steadily wins:} Qb3 28. Qa5 f6 29. Bg3 Bb7 30. Rc7 Rc8 31. h3 Rxc7 32. Rxc7 Re8 33. Qc5 Qd5 34. f3 Qxc5 35. dxc5 Bd5 36. Ra7 Rc8 37. e4 Bb3 38. Bf2 Bxa4 39. Rxe7 Bb5 40. Bd4 Rf8 41. Rc7 a5 (41... Rf7 42. Rc8+ Rf8 43. Rxf8+ Kxf8 44. Bxf6 $18 {}) 42. Rb7 Be8 43. Rb6 f5 44. exf5 gxf5 45. c6 Kf7 46. Bc5 Rg8 47. Rb7+ Ke6 48. Rb8 Bf7 49. c7 Kd7 50. Bb6 Rc8 51. Bxa5 Be6 52. Kf2 1-0


