{This was my first win against a 2700+ opponent.} 1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. Nf3 e6 5. Be2 Ne7 6. O-O c5 7. c4 dxc4 $5 (7... Nbc6 8. dxc5 d4 {This is the mainline.}) 8. Na3 Nbc6 9. Nxc4 Nd5 10. dxc5 $6 $146 {This was played over the board.} (10. Bg5 $5) 10... Bxc5 11. Bg5 Qc7 12. Rc1 O-O 13. Qb3 (13. a3 h6 14. b4 $5 Bxf2+ 15. Rxf2 hxg5 16. b5 g4 17. bxc6 gxf3 18. Bxf3 bxc6 19. Nd6 $44) (13. Nh4 $5) 13... h6 14. Ne3 $6 (14. Be3 Be7 $15 (14... Nxe3 15. Nxe3 Bxe3 16. Qxe3 {transposes to the game})) 14... Bxe3 $6 {Now he thought for 25 minutes.} (14... hxg5 $1 {I thought I had many options.} 15. Nxd5 (15. Rxc5 Nf4 $17) 15... exd5 16. Rxc5 Qe7 $1 {I missed this move during the game} 17. Qc3 (17. Rfc1 g4 18. Nd2 Rfd8 $1 $17 19. Rxd5 $2 Rxd5 20. Qxd5 Rd8 $19) (17. Qxd5 $2 Rfd8 18. Qc4 g4 19. Ne1 Nd4 {[%cal Yd4e2]} 20. Bd3 b5 $19) 17... Rac8 $15) 15. Bxe3 Nxe3 16. Qxe3 {Praggnanandhaa,R: 'transposes to the game'} Qb6 $1 17. Qxb6 axb6 18. a3 Be4 (18... Bg4 $5 19. h3 Bh5 (19... Bxf3 20. Bxf3 Nxe5 21. Bxb7 $11) 20. Rc3 $11) 19. Nd2 Nd4 20. Rfe1 Bd5 21. Bd3 Rfd8 22. Rc3 g5 $1 23. Ne4 Bxe4 24. Rxe4 (24. Bxe4 $4 Ne2+ $1 $19) 24... Ra5 25. b4 Rad5 26. Bc4 R5d7 (26... Rc8 $5 27. Bxd5 Rxc3 28. h4 $1 Nc6 (28... Nf5 29. Bxb7 Nxh4 30. a4 Ra3 31. Bc6 $11) 29. Bxc6 bxc6 30. hxg5 hxg5 31. Re3 $11) 27. Bf1 Nf5 28. g3 Rd1 29. Kg2 Ra1 30. Bd3 Kg7 (30... Ne7 $5 31. h4 Nd5 32. Rb3 $11) 31. h4 gxh4 $2 (31... Rd4 32. Rxd4 Nxd4 33. hxg5 hxg5 34. Be4 Nb5 35. Rc8 Rxa3 36. Rb8 Rb3 37. Rxb7 Rxb4 38. Rxb6 (38. Bc6 Nd4 39. Be8 Kf8 40. Bxf7 Rb5 41. Bh5 Rxe5 42. Rxb6 $11) 38... Rxe4 39. Rxb5 $11) 32. Rg4+ Kh7 33. Bxf5+ exf5 34. Rxh4 Re8 35. Rc7 Kg7 36. Rxb7 $6 (36. Rd4 $3 {The engine's suggestion} Rxe5 37. Rdd7 Kg6 (37... Rxa3 38. Rxf7+ Kg6 39. Rg7+ Kf6 40. Rh7 $1 Kg6 41. Rcg7+ Kf6 42. Rf7+ Ke6 43. Rxb7 $18) 38. Rxf7 Re6 $1 39. Rg7+ Kf6 40. Rh7 Ke5 41. Rc2 $1 Rc6 $1 (41... Rxa3 $2 42. Re2+ Kd6 43. Rxe6+ Kxe6 44. Rxh6+ Kd7 45. Rxb6 Kc7 46. Rb5 $18) 42. Re2+ (42. Rxc6 $2 bxc6 43. Rxh6 c5 $13) 42... Kd5 43. Rd7+ Kc4 44. Re3 $18) 36... Rxe5 37. Rxb6 Rxa3 38. Rbxh6 Re4 39. Rh7+ Kg8 40. Rh8+ Kg7 {Praggnanandhaa,R: '=' Praggnanandhaa,R: 'This is even easier way to draw. The king will not be exposed.'} 41. R8h7+ Kf8 (41... Kg8 42. Rxe4 fxe4 43. Rh4 e3 44. fxe3 Rxe3 45. Rh6 Rb3 46. Rb6 Kg7 47. b5 Kf8 48. Rb7 f5 49. b6 Ke8 50. Rb8+ Kd7 51. b7 Kc6 52. Rf8 Rxb7 $11) 42. Rh8+ Ke7 (42... Kg7 $11 {This is even easier way to draw. The king will not be exposed.}) 43. Rc8 Rb3 $2 (43... Ra2 $1 44. Rc4 Re5 45. Rh7 Kf6 46. Rc7 Ree2 $1 {Now he has this move.}) 44. Rc4 Re5 45. Rh7 $1 Rb5 (45... Kf6 {Best try} 46. Rc7 Rxb4 47. Rcxf7+ Ke6 48. Ra7 $18) 46. Rc7+ Ke6 47. Rh6+ f6 48. Rc6+ $18 Ke5 49. Rhxf6 R3xb4 50. Rfe6+ $6 (50. Rcd6 $1 {[%cal Yf6e6] This move wins on the spot.} Rd5 (50... f4 51. g4 $18) 51. f4+ Ke4 52. Rxd5 Kxd5 53. Rxf5+ $18) 50... Kd4 51. Rcd6+ Rd5 52. Rxd5+ $4 (52. Ra6 $18) 52... Kxd5 53. Re2 {I thought this position is winning.} f4 $4 {He was in time trouble.} (53... Rb7 $1 54. f3 (54. Kf3 Rb4 $11 {[%cal Ya4h4]}) 54... Rb8 55. f4 (55. g4 fxg4 56. fxg4 Rg8 $11) 55... Rf8 $1 $11) 54. g4 $18 Rb3 55. f3 Rb8 56. Re4 Rf8 57. Kf2 Rf7 58. Ke2 Rf6 59. Kd3 Rf8 60. Ra4 Rb8 61. Rxf4 Rb3+ 62. Ke2 Ke5 63. Rf5+ Kd4 64. Kf2 1-0


