1. d4 {Arsovic,Goran} Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nf3 Bg7 4. g3 c6 5. Nc3 d5 6. Qb3 O-O 7. Bg2 Qb6 8. O-O Rd8 9. Bd2 {A rare move, White wants to play fc1, e3, a4.} (9. Na4 {is more popular than 9.d2 and White can get the same pawn structure:} Qxb3 10. axb3 Na6 11. Bf4 (11. Bd2 Ne8 (11... Ne4 $5 12. Bf4 Bf5 13. Rfc1 h6 14. Nc3 g5 15. Be3 Nb4 16. Ra4 a5 $11) 12. e3 Bf5 13. Rfc1 Nec7 14. Ba5 Rdc8 15. Bf1 Bg4 16. Ne1 dxc4 17. bxc4 e5 18. h3 Bd7 19. dxe5 Bxe5 20. Nd3 $14 {Burmakin,V (2505)-Dhulipalla,B (2335) Barbera del Valles 2017 1/2 (83)}) 11... Ne8 (11... Be6 12. Rfc1 Ne8 13. h3 dxc4 14. bxc4 Bxd4 $5 {Sagar Shah: 'Howell decides to pick up a pawn at the cost of giving up his strong dark-squared bishop'.} 15. Nxd4 Rxd4 16. b3 $14 {1/2 (78) Pert,N (2569)-Howell, D (2693) London 2015 CBM 170 [Sagar Shah/CB Website] Of course White has excellent compensation thanks to his two bishops and also because none of the Black's minor pieces are really in the game.}) 12. Nc3 Nac7 13. Ra4 a6 14. Rd1 Be6 15. h3 Rac8 16. c5 h6 17. g4 g5 18. Bh2 f5 19. gxf5 Bxf5 20. Ne5 Nf6 $11 {Wojtaszek,R (2748)-Ragger,M (2688) Reykjavik 2015 0-1 (44)}) (9. h3 {(Arsovic,Goran) - 134/150}) 9... Be6 {Black has other options.} (9... Bf5 10. Na4 Qxb3 11. axb3 Nbd7 12. Rfc1 Be4 13. Be1 Ne8 14. e3 Nd6 {I don't really understand what exactly Black wants by playing this} (14... e6 $5 15. Bb4 Bf8 16. Bxf8 Kxf8 $11) 15. Bb4 a5 16. Be1 (16. Ba3 $1 Bf8 17. Nc3 Bxf3 18. Bxf3 e6 19. Be2 $14) 16... e6 17. Ra2 b5 (17... dxc4 $1 18. bxc4 Nxc4 19. Rxc4 Bd5 20. Nd2 b5 21. Bxd5 cxd5 22. Rc6 bxa4 23. Rxa4 Rdb8 $11) 18. cxb5 cxb5 19. Nc5 Nxc5 20. dxc5 $14 {Chandra,A (2464)-Zierk,S (2488) Saint Louis 2016 1/2 (76)}) (9... dxc4 10. Qxc4 Be6 11. Qd3 Bg4 (11... Na6 $5 12. b3 c5 13. Na4 Qc7 14. Rac1 Bf5 $11 15. Qb5 Bd7 16. Qa5 $1 (16. Qc4 Be6 17. Qd3 Bf5 $11) 16... Qxa5 17. Bxa5 b6 18. Nxb6 axb6 19. Bxb6 Rdc8 20. Ne5 $14) 12. Na4 Qa6 13. Nc5 Qxd3 14. Nxd3 Bxf3 15. Bxf3 Rxd4 16. Bc3 Rd8 17. Nc5 b6 18. Rfd1 $44 {Ashwath,R (2239)-Kozul,Z (2607) Sitges ESP 2017 0-1 (75)}) (9... Na6 10. Rfc1 Ne4 11. Qxb6 axb6 12. cxd5 Nxc3 13. bxc3 Rxd5 14. Ne5 Rd8 15. Nc4 b5 16. Nb6 Ra7 17. a4 bxa4 18. Rxa4 Be6 19. Be3 Kf8 20. Rb1 Ke8 21. Bf4 Bf5 22. Rba1 c5 23. e3 Bd7 24. Ra5 cxd4 25. cxd4 Bf5 26. Bc7 Nxc7 27. Rxa7 e5 28. Rxb7 Ne6 {1-0 (28) Dreev,A (2653)-Ghasi,A (2475) chess.com INT 2018}) (9... Bg4 10. e3 e6 11. h3 Bxf3 12. Bxf3 Nbd7 13. Rfd1 $14) 10. Na4 Qxb3 11. axb3 {After 9.a4 xb3 10.axb3 Black should play 10...a6. Now this move is dubious.} Na6 $6 {This knight will be misplaced till the end of the game. White's plan is fc1, e3, f1, a5 and if ...b6 then xb6. Black's knight would be better placed on d7.} (11... Nbd7 {looks better than 11...a6:} 12. Rfc1 Ne4 {As an improvement Black can consider 12...a6 or 12...h6.} (12... a6 $5 13. Ng5 {Since 13.cxd5 xd5 doesn't give White any advantage} (13. cxd5 Bxd5 14. b4 Bxf3 15. Bxf3 e5 $11) 13... Bf5 14. cxd5 cxd5 15. Rc7 h6 16. Nf3 b5 17. Nc3 (17. Nc5 $6 Nxc5 18. dxc5 Ne4 $15) 17... b4 18. Na4 a5 $11) (12... h6 {Black wants to take on d5 with the bishop.} 13. e3 (13. Bb4 Re8 14. e3 a6 15. Nd2 Rac8 16. Nc3 Bf8 {Black should get an equal position}) 13... Ne4 14. Ba5 Rdc8 15. Nd2 f5) 13. Ba5 b6 {Black's knight is on d7, so Why doesn't have xb6.} 14. Be1 Rac8 15. cxd5 Bxd5 16. b4 e5 17. Nxe5 Nxe5 18. dxe5 Bxe5 19. Bxe4 $5 (19. Nc3 Nxc3 20. Bxc3 Bxc3 21. Rxc3 Bxg2 22. Kxg2 Rc7 $11) 19... Bxe4 20. Nc3 Bd5 (20... Bf5 $5 21. Rxa7 b5 22. e3 Bg7 $44) 21. Rxa7 Bc4 $44 {Giri,A (2773)-So,W (2808) Wijk aan Zee 2017 1/2 (43)}) 12. Rfc1 {Despite the fact that the computer evaluates the position as equal, It seems to me that Black's position is already unpleasant.} Ne4 $146 {Arsovic,Goran: 'Diagram [#]'} ({Mohamed Haddouche tried} 12... Ne8 13. e3 h6 14. Ba5 Rdc8 15. Nd2 Nec7 16. Bf1 {Arsovic,Goran: ''} (16. Bxc7 $1 Rxc7 (16... Nxc7 17. Nc5 $16) 17. cxd5 Bxd5 (17... cxd5 18. Rxc7 Nxc7 19. Nc5 b6 20. Nxe6 fxe6 21. f4 $16 {Black's bishop is locked in}) 18. Bf1 b5 19. Nc3 $16) 16... Bd7 17. Bxc7 Rxc7 18. cxd5 cxd5 19. Bxa6 Rxc1+ 20. Rxc1 bxa6 21. Rc7 Bxa4 22. bxa4 $16 {1-0 (46) Ding,L (2777)-Haddouche,M (2487) Tbilisi 2017}) 13. Ba5 {Arsovic,Goran: '!?'} Rdc8 ({Black could have tried} 13... b6 $5 {I think it is Black's best chance to level the game:} 14. Be1 ({White could have got only problems after} 14. Bxb6 axb6 15. Nxb6 $17 Ra7 16. Ra4 dxc4 (16... Rb8 17. c5 Naxc5 18. Rxa7 Nxb3 19. Rxc6 Bxd4 20. Nxd4 Nxd4 21. Rxe6 fxe6 22. Ra8 Rxa8 23. Nxa8 Nxe2+ 24. Kf1 Nd4 25. Bxe4 dxe4 26. Nb6 $11) 17. bxc4 Nd2 $5 18. Nxd2 Bxd4 19. c5 Bxc5 20. Nbc4 Nb4 $15) 14... c5 15. Ne5 (15. Nc3 {Arsovic,Goran} Nc7 (15... Nxc3 16. Bxc3 (16. bxc3 $5 Nc7 17. dxc5 dxc4 (17... bxc5 18. Ng5 $16) 18. bxc4 bxc5 19. Nd2 Rac8 20. Rxa7 $14) 16... cxd4 17. Nxd4 Nc5 18. Nxe6 fxe6 19. Ra3 $14) 16. e3 f5 17. h4 h6 18. Ne2 $14) 15... Rac8 16. cxd5 (16. Nxb6 axb6 17. Rxa6 cxd4 18. Nd3 Nc5 $11) 16... Bxd5 17. Nc3 Nxc3 18. bxc3 Bxg2 19. Kxg2 cxd4 20. cxd4 Rxc1 21. Rxc1 Bxe5 22. dxe5 Nc5 $11) 14. e3 g5 ({Now Black can't play} 14... b6 $2 {because of} 15. Bxb6 axb6 16. Nxb6 Nc7 17. Nxa8 Rxa8 18. Rxa8+ Nxa8 19. Ra1 Nc7 20. Ra7 $18) (14... f5 15. Bf1 Bf7 16. Ne5 Bxe5 17. dxe5 Nac5 18. Nxc5 Nxc5 19. Ra3 $14) 15. Nd2 {Arsovic,Goran: '!'} Nxd2 (15... Nd6 {is not better, due to} 16. cxd5 Bxd5 17. Bf1 Nb5 18. Nc3 $16) 16. Bxd2 g4 17. Bf1 {Arsovic,Goran: '' I think that 17.cxd5 or 17.b4 was stronger:} (17. cxd5 $5 Bxd5 18. Bxd5 cxd5 19. b4 e5 20. Rxc8+ Rxc8 21. dxe5 Bxe5 22. b5 Nc7 23. Bc3 Bxc3 24. Nxc3 $16) (17. b4 $5 dxc4 18. b5 cxb5 19. Bxb7 bxa4 20. Bxa6 Rcb8 21. Bc3 $16 {White is much better.}) 17... dxc4 $6 {This changes the pawn structure in White's favour.} (17... Bf5 18. cxd5 cxd5 19. Rxc8+ Rxc8 (19... Bxc8 {Arsovic,Goran} 20. Ba5 $1 e5 (20... b6 $2 21. Bxb6 $18) (20... Bd7 21. b4 Bxa4 22. Rxa4 Nb8 23. Bb6 Na6 24. Bc5 Nxc5 25. bxc5 $16) 21. dxe5 Bxe5 22. Bc3 $14) 20. Bxa6 bxa6 21. Nc5 {Arsovic,Goran: ''} e5 22. Bc3 exd4 23. exd4 Bf8 $14 {Black has good chances to make a draw.}) 18. bxc4 c5 {Arsovic,Goran: '?!'} (18... Bf5 {Arsovic,Goran} 19. Bg2 (19. b4 e5 20. b5 cxb5 21. cxb5 Nc7 22. dxe5 Bxe5 23. Bc3 $14) 19... e5 20. e4 Bd7 21. d5 Bf8 22. Be3 $14) 19. Bg2 $1 Rab8 20. d5 Bd7 21. Bc3 $1 {Arsovic,Goran: '' White has an extra pawn in the centre and Black's knight is stuck on a6.} Bxa4 ({David could have tried} 21... Bf5 22. Bxg7 Kxg7 23. e4 Bg6 24. Nc3 Rd8 25. h3 $16) (21... Rd8 {Arsovic,Goran} 22. Bxg7 Kxg7 23. Nc3 $16) 22. Rxa4 Rd8 {Arsovic,Goran: 'Diagram [#]'} 23. h3 $1 gxh3 $8 ({After} 23... h5 24. hxg4 hxg4 25. Bf1 {Black will lose the g4-pawn.} (25. Be4 {Arsovic,Goran} e6 26. dxe6 (26. Kg2 f5 27. Bc2 $16) 26... fxe6 27. Ra5 $16)) 24. Bxh3 Rd6 25. e4 Bxc3 26. Rxc3 $16 ({Richard could even consider} 26. bxc3 $5 Rb6 27. e5 {with a big advantage.}) 26... Rb6 27. b3 e5 {Now White can get a strong centre.} 28. Rf3 (28. f4 $1 f6 (28... Re8 {Arsovic,Goran} 29. Bf5 $16) 29. Rf3 Kg7 30. Ra5) 28... Kg7 29. Ra5 h6 30. Bd7 Rd6 31. Bb5 Nc7 $6 ({The last chance was} 31... Nb4 $5 32. Rxa7 Nc2 {Black has sacrificed the a-pawn and got some counterplay. Now Black's knight is better than White's bishop.} 33. Rd3 h5 34. Ra5 Nd4 $16 {Black has managed to put his knight in the centre. However sooner or later White will prepare f4 with good chances to win the game.}) 32. Ba4 {Arsovic,Goran: '!'} (32. Rxa7 {Arsovic,Goran} Nxb5 33. cxb5 Rb6 34. Ra5 $18) 32... Na6 $8 33. Rf5 f6 34. f4 exf4 35. gxf4 Kg6 {Arsovic,Goran: 'Diagram [#]'} 36. b4 $1 Nxb4 (36... cxb4 37. c5 Rdd8 38. Bd1 b3 (38... Nc7 39. Rxa7 $18) (38... Kg7 {Arsovic,Goran} 39. Kf2 $18) 39. Bxb3 Re8 40. Bc2 Nb4 41. Bb1 $18) 37. Bd1 $18 {Arsovic,Goran: '+-!'} Na6 (37... Ra6 38. Rxa6 Nxa6 39. Bh5+ Kg7 40. e5 fxe5 41. Rf7+ Kg8 42. fxe5 $18) 38. Bh5+ Kh7 39. e5 Rb6 40. Rb5 {This is a reliable way to win the game.} ({The computer recommend} 40. e6 Rg8+ 41. Kf2 Rb2+ 42. Kf3 Rh2 (42... Rgg2 43. Rxf6 Rbf2+ 44. Ke3 $18) (42... Rb3+ {Arsovic,Goran} 43. Ke4 $18) 43. d6 $18) 40... Rg8+ 41. Kf2 Rxb5 42. cxb5 