1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nf6 5. Nxf6+ exf6 6. c3 Bd6 7. Bd3 O-O 8. Qc2 Re8+ 9. Ne2 h5 10. Be3 {The bishop is more active here than on d2 and the d-pawn is reinforced.} Nd7 11. O-O-O Nf8 12. Kb1 Be6 13. c4 Rc8 $1 {Preparing ...b5.} (13... b5 $6 {Offering a pawn to open queenside lines fails tactically due to} 14. d5 $1 cxd5 15. c5 $1 Rc8 16. Bxb5 $16) 14. h3 (14. Nc3 {Blocking the c-file is logical to prevent the intended ...b5 advance.} Bb4 $1 {Preparing the ...b5 advance to open up queenside lines.} (14... b5 {1/2 (31) Boixader Arbo,X (2099)-Hansen,T (2429) Barcelona 2017} 15. cxb5 $1 cxb5 16. Bxb5 Bd7 17. Bxd7 Nxd7 18. d5 $14 {Black does not have enough compensation for the pawn}) 15. Ne4 {Intending c4-c5 and d6.} Be7 $1 {The battle for and against the ...b5 advance continues.} (15... b5 $2 16. c5 $16) 16. Nc3 (16. Rhe1 $6 b5 17. c5 {0-1 (30) Cumming,R (2162)-Hansen,T (2408) London 2017} g6 $1 18. Nc3 (18. h3 f5 19. Nc3 Bf6 $15) 18... Qa5 $15 {Increasing the pressure on the queenside with the immediate threat ...b4} (18... f5 19. d5 $1 {a nice breakthrough idea} Bxd5 20. Bxb5 Qa5 21. Nxd5 Qxb5 22. Nxe7+ Rxe7 23. Qc3 $14 {Black has problems on the dark squares.})) 16... Bb4 17. Ne4 $11 {with a repetition of moves.}) 14... h4 {Preventing g2-g4 is one of the fundamental ideas behind the quick ...h5 advance.} 15. Rdg1 (15. Qd2 Ng6 16. Nc3 $6 Bb4 $1 $15 17. a3 Bxc3 18. Qxc3 b5 19. d5 cxd5 20. c5 a6 21. Bc2 {Aryan,C (2509)-Svane,R (2586) Moscow RUS 2018} Ne7 $17 {followed by ...f5 and Black is completely fine.}) (15. Nc3 {looks best but has not yet been played to date:} Ng6 {Black's idea is ...e7.} 16. Rhe1 (16. Bxg6 $6 fxg6 17. Qxg6 Bxc4 $17) 16... Ne7 $132) 15... b5 16. c5 Bb8 17. Nc3 b4 18. Ne4 f5 19. Nd6 Bxd6 20. cxd6 Qxd6 21. Bxf5 Qd5 22. Bxe6 Nxe6 $17 {Black has a clear advantage with the better structure and the superior minor piece.} 23. Rd1 Qxg2 24. Qf5 Qd5 25. Qg4 Nf8 26. Qxh4 Qe4+ 27. Qxe4 Rxe4 28. Kc2 Ng6 29. h4 Nxh4 30. Kd3 Rg4 31. Kc4 c5 32. Kb3 cxd4 33. Rxd4 Rxd4 34. Bxd4 Nf3 35. Bxa7 g5 36. Kxb4 Ra8 37. Be3 Rxa2 38. Kb3 Ra8 39. Kc2 Rc8+ 40. Kd3 Rb8 41. Ke4 g4 42. Kf5 Rxb2 43. Kxg4 Ne5+ 44. Kf5 Ng6 45. Ke4 1/2-1/2


