1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nd5 {The Belgrade Gambit.} Be7 {Solid,} (5... Nb4 {is also a good reply.}) 6. Nxd4 O-O (6... Nxd5 {is more normal,} 7. exd5 Nxd4 8. Qxd4 O-O 9. Be2 Bf6 10. Qd1 d6 11. O-O Bf5 12. Bd3 Qd7 13. c3 Rfe8 14. a4 Be4 15. Bxe4 Rxe4 16. Qb3 c5 17. dxc6 bxc6 18. Be3 Rae8 19. Rad1 d5 20. Qc2 Be5 $15 {Sax-Karpov, Tilburg, 1979}) 7. Nb5 Bc5 $5 {David's novelty, prepared that morning.} (7... Nxd5 8. exd5 a6 9. Nc3 (9. dxc6 axb5 10. Bxb5 dxc6 {looks good for Black, although a draw was agreed here in Tsiamis, K (2282)-Goritsas, C (2260)/Ermioni Argolidas 2005.}) 9... Ne5 10. Be2 {leaves White some extra space, but nothing serious.}) (7... Nxe4 8. Bc4 (8. Nbxc7 Bc5 {transposes to the game}) 8... Bb4+ 9. c3 Nxf2 10. Qh5 Nxh1 11. cxb4 {was Kenworthy-Van der Sterren, Ramsgate, 1981, when} Re8+ 12. Be3 d6 13. O-O-O Re4 {is unclear.}) 8. Nbxc7 {After an hour's thought!} Nxe4 $1 9. Bd3 $6 (9. Qf3 $6 Nxf2 10. Be3 Bxe3 11. Nxe3 Nxh1 12. Nxa8 Qh4+ 13. Kd2 Qb4+ 14. c3 Qxb2+ 15. Nc2 d5 16. Bd3 {Mahjoob, M (2337)-Croad, N/Yerevan 2000, when the simple} Ne5 $1 {wins, e.g.} 17. Bxh7+ (17. Qxd5 Nxd3 18. Qxd3 Nf2 19. Qd4 Bf5) 17... Kxh7 18. Qh5+ Kg8 19. Qxe5 Nf2 20. Nc7 Ne4+ 21. Kd3 Bf5 22. Qxf5 Qxc3+ 23. Ke2 Qxc2+) (9. Be3 {is probably the only move,} Bxe3 10. fxe3 Rb8 (10... Qh4+ $2 11. g3 Nxg3 12. hxg3 Qxh1 13. Nxa8 {with an extra piece.}) 11. Qh5 g6 12. Qf3 f5 13. Bd3 Ne5 14. Qh3 d6 15. O-O Nc5 16. Be2 Bd7 {and if anything I prefer Black.}) 9... Nxf2 10. Bxh7+ Kxh7 11. Qh5+ Kg8 12. Bg5 $2 (12. Rf1 {is the only try, but even so} Re8+ $1 13. Nxe8 Qxe8+ 14. Qe2 Qxe2+ 15. Kxe2 Ng4 {should win, the two pieces are much better than the rook.}) 12... Re8+ $1 13. Kf1 (13. Nxe8 Qxe8+ 14. Be7 d6 $1 (14... Nxe7 $5 15. Nc7 d5 $3 16. Nxe8 Bg4 17. Qg5 Rxe8 {also wins.}) 15. O-O Be6 {winning material.}) 13... Re5 $1 (13... Re5 $1 14. Bxd8 Rxh5 15. Nxa8 Nxh1 {wins two pieces.}) 0-1


