{[%evp 0,114,16,-12,38,39,30,22,23,16,16,38,34,13,51,74,56,36,34,27,33,30,30,33,54,55,57,13,28,28,28,19,50,50,79,10,96,41,83,82,81,102,114,87,96,90,114,18,96,36,95,68,182,172,172,162,162,162,110,103,84,-5,12,51,108,46,47,17,17,-31,0,0,0,0,0,-21,304,284,280,280,280,280,329,329,337,352,366,333,368,299,387,413,413,413,413,407,415,406,406,406,402,402,406,402,406,274,295,290,281,247,248,253,446,1028,1064,1281,1288]} 1. c4 c6 2. Nc3 d5 3. d4 Nf6 4. cxd5 cxd5 5. Bf4 Nc6 6. e3 Bg4 7. Qb3 Na5 8. Qa4+ Bd7 9. Qc2 Rc8 10. Bd3 e6 11. Nf3 b5 {This looks agressive but actually is double-edged as the advances on the queenside also can become weaknesses.} (11... Be7 12. O-O O-O 13. Ne5 {we will look at this line in the video on the game between Glud-Andersen}) 12. a3 (12. Qe2 {But I am not convinced white can play for an advantage after Has done very well in practice.} b4 13. Nd1 Nc4) 12... Be7 {Black decides it is time to finish the development.} 13. Qe2 $5 {A very clever move.} a6 {One of the main points is that this pawn might get weak after a subsequent a3-a4, like we will see in the game.} (13... b4 14. axb4 Bxb4 15. O-O Bxc3 $2 (15... O-O 16. Bg5 Be7 17. Ne5 $16 {white has a big initiative}) 16. bxc3 Rxc3 17. Qd2 $18) 14. Ne5 O-O 15. O-O Qb6 (15... Be8 $1 {this is the best but now the rook is stuck on f8} 16. a4) 16. a4 $6 (16. Bg5 $1 {and black is already close to being lost.} Qd8 {the only move to avoid immediate disaster} (16... Be8 17. Qf3 Qd8 (17... h6 18. Bxf6 Bxf6 19. Nxd5 exd5 20. Qf5 g6 21. Qxc8 $18) 18. Qh3 h6 19. Bxh6 gxh6 20. Qxh6 $18) (16... Rfd8 $2 17. Bxh7+ Kxh7 18. Bxf6 Bxf6 19. Qh5+ Kg8 20. Qxf7+ Kh7 21. Nxd7 $18) 17. f4 $16) 16... b4 17. Nb1 Ra8 $2 (17... Nb3 18. Nxd7 Nxd7 19. Bxh7+ Kxh7 20. Qd3+ Kg8 21. Qxb3 Qc6 22. Nd2 Qc2 23. Rfd1 Qxb3 24. Nxb3 Rc2 25. Rd2 Rfc8 $44) 18. Bg5 Be8 19. Nd2 $16 h6 20. Bh4 Rc8 21. b3 (21. Rfb1 $1 {easier for engines than for humans!} Ra8 22. Rc1) 21... Rc3 22. Rab1 $14 Qc7 23. f3 Bd6 24. f4 Be7 25. Rfd1 Ne4 {it is hard to come up with a good move for black} 26. Bxe7 Qxe7 27. Bxe4 dxe4 28. Nxe4 Rxb3 29. Rxb3 Nxb3 30. Rb1 $2 (30. Qxa6 f6 31. Nd3 Bg6 32. Nef2) 30... f6 31. Nc4 Bg6 32. Nxf6+ gxf6 33. Rxb3 Rc8 {Black is completely back in the game.} 34. e4 Qd7 35. d5 exd5 36. exd5 Qxd5 37. Qg4 Rc7 $4 {Not sure what black missed here.} (37... Qc5+ 38. Ne3 Kh7 {and it is white who has to fight for a draw}) 38. Qxg6+ $18 Rg7 39. Qe8+ Kh7 40. Qe2 Rxg2+ 41. Qxg2 Qd1+ 42. Kf2 Qxb3 43. Qe4+ Kg7 44. Nd6 Qc3 45. Qe7+ Kg8 46. Ne8 Qd4+ 47. Kg2 Qd5+ 48. Kg3 Qf7 49. Nxf6+ Kg7 50. Ne8+ Kg8 51. Nf6+ Kg7 52. Qxf7+ Kxf7 53. Nd5 b3 54. f5 b2 55. Nc3 h5 56. h4 Ke7 57. Kf4 Kd6 {1-0 Black resigns.} 1-0


