1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Bf5 5. Ng3 Bg6 6. h4 h6 7. Nf3 e6 8. h5 Bh7 9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Nf6 11. Bd2 c5 (11... Nbd7 {transposes to 7...Nd7 territory of course.}) (11... Be7 12. O-O-O O-O (12... c5 13. Ne4 cxd4 14. Nxd4 Nbd7 15. Nxf6+ (15. Kb1 {is probably a better try. In one game, Black fell for a trap immediately:} O-O 16. Nxf6+ Nxf6 $6 (16... Bxf6 17. Nb3 $16) 17. Bxh6 gxh6 18. Qg3+ Kh8 19. Nxe6 $16 {1-0 (42) Kokarev,D (2628)-Gavrilov,A (2456) Moscow 2014}) 15... Nxf6 16. Qb5+ Qd7 17. Qxd7+ Kxd7 18. Bf4 {1-0 (43) Shomoev, A (2552)-Ganguly,S (2652) Ulaanbaatar 2018} Rhd8 $1 {since} 19. Nf5+ Ke8 20. Nxg7+ Kf8 21. Bxh6 Kg8 {forces White to return material.}) 13. Ne4 Nxe4 14. Qxe4 Qd5 15. Qg4 Kh8 16. Kb1 Nd7 17. Qh3 Rad8 18. g4 $40 {0-1 (64) Wei,Y (2706) -Ding,L (2755) China 2015}) 12. O-O-O (12. Ne4 {is less common, but better.} Nc6 (12... Nxe4 $6 13. Qxe4 Nc6 14. dxc5 Bxc5 15. O-O-O Qe7 {0-1 (59) Rogic,D  (2523)-Zelcic,R (2555) Stari Mikanovci 2009} 16. Qg4 f5 17. Qg3 $14) (12... Nbd7 $6 13. dxc5 Nxe4 14. Qxe4 Nxc5 15. Qc4 Qb6 16. O-O-O Rc8 17. Kb1 $16) 13. Bc3 {now the simplest is} cxd4 (13... Nb4 14. Nxf6+ gxf6 15. Qe2 (15. Bxb4 cxb4 16. c4 {1/2-1/2 (51) Inarkiev,E (2680)-Artemiev,V (2701) Sharjah 2018} (16. d5 Qxd5 17. Qxd5 exd5 {1-0 (47) Quesada Perez,Y (2538)-Gonzalez Vidal,Y (2565) Santa Clara 2019} 18. Rh4 O-O-O 19. Rf4 $44) 16... bxc3 17. bxc3 Qd5 $132) 15... Nd5 16. Bd2 cxd4 17. Nxd4 Qb6 18. O-O-O Rc8 {1/2-1/2 (49) Spasov,V (2542) -Genov,P (2483) Sofia 2004} 19. Be1 $36) 14. Nxd4 Nb4 15. Nxf6+ gxf6 16. Qb5+ Qd7 17. Bxb4 {Meek.} (17. Qxd7+ Kxd7 18. Rd1 Nd5 19. Bd2 Rc8 20. c3 {White could well have a slight pull here. Objectively, Black's position must hold up though.}) 17... Qxb5 18. Nxb5 Bxb4+ 19. c3 Ba5 20. Nd6+ Ke7 $11 {0-1 (49) Nemcova,K (2313)-Lei,T (2488) Khanty-Mansiysk 2017 note that} 21. Nxb7 {is bad in view of} Bb6 22. Rd1 Rhg8 23. g3 Rab8 24. Nd6 Rgd8 $19) 12... Nc6 13. Bc3 (13. Be3 Qa5 14. Kb1 Be7 15. dxc5 Bxc5 16. Ne4 Nxe4 17. Qxe4 Bxe3 18. Qxe3 O-O $11) 13... Qd5 $1 14. dxc5 (14. Kb1 {is provocative -} c4 15. Qe2 b5 16. Nf1 Nb4 17. Ne3 (17. a3 $2 a5 $17) 17... Qb7 18. Ne5 Nbd5 $132) 14... Qxd3 15. cxd3 (15. Rxd3 Bxc5 16. Bxf6 gxf6 17. Ne4 Be7 $11) 15... Bxc5 16. Bxf6 gxf6 17. d4 Bb6 18. d5 Ne7 19. dxe6 fxe6 20. Ne4 Nd5 21. Nh4 (21. Nd4 Bxd4 22. Rxd4 Ke7 $11) 21... O-O-O (21... O-O 22. Ng6 Rfd8 23. g4 Rac8+ 24. Kb1 Rc4 25. f3 Kg7 {and Black is the one with the initiative.}) 22. g4 Rhf8 23. Kb1 f5 {A sensible decision to make a draw.} 24. gxf5 exf5 25. Ng3 Bxf2 26. Ngxf5 Bxh4 27. Nxh4 Nf4 28. Rc1+ Kb8 29. Ng6 Rf6 30. Rcf1 Nxh5 31. Rxf6 Nxf6 32. Rxh6 1/2-1/2


