1. e4 {GM Davorin Kuljasevic} c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Bd3 Nc6 5. c3 Qc7 {Last month, I only discussed setups in which Black's knight comes to f6 immediately.} 6. h3 (6. Ne2 Bg4 7. f3 Bd7 $11) 6... g6 7. Qc2 {GM Davorin Kuljasevic: '?!' GM Davorin Kuljasevic: 'This prophylactic move is wrong here.'} (7. Nf3 Bf5 8. O-O Nf6 9. Re1 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Bg7 $11 {is unproblematic. 1-0 (85) Van Foreest,L (2481)-Tari,A (2599) Wijk aan Zee 2018}) (7. Ne2 {is probably best. One game saw Black neutralise White's play.} Bf5 8. Bf4 (8. Bxf5 {GM Davorin Kuljasevic} gxf5 {typical structure with gxf5 (Dominguez-Mamedyarov)}) 8... Qb6 9. Bxf5 gxf5 10. Qb3 (10. O-O e6) 10... e6 11. Na3 Nf6 12. Nb5 Rc8 13. Nd6+ Bxd6 14. Bxd6 Rg8 15. O-O Nxd4 16. cxd4 Qxd6 17. Qxb7 Rc7 18. Qb3 Ke7 $11 {1-0 (30) Van Foreest,L (2499)-Janik,I (2453) Porto Carras 2018}) 7... f6 $1 {GM Davorin Kuljasevic: 'without the knight on f6, this move is now strong, preparing ...e7-e5. White does not have a good way of stopping it.'} (7... Bg7 8. Nf3 {leads to normal play of course.}) 8. Ne2 (8. f4 {(GM Davorin Kuljasevic) [#]} Nh6 $1 9. Ne2 Bf5 $15) (8. Nf3 {GM Davorin Kuljasevic} e5 9. dxe5 fxe5 10. O-O e4 $17) 8... e5 9. O-O Nge7 {GM Davorin Kuljasevic: '=' GM Davorin Kuljasevic: 'Black has equalized comfortably out of the opening.'} 10. dxe5 (10. Qa4 Bd7 11. dxe5 fxe5 12. Na3 (12. c4 $2 e4 (12... Nd4 13. Qd1 dxc4 14. Be4 Bg7 $15) 13. cxd5 exd3 14. dxc6 Qxc6 15. Qxc6 Nxc6 16. Nf4 O-O-O $15) 12... a6 13. c4 O-O-O $5 {What a mess!} (13... d4 14. b4 Bg7 15. Qb3 {is a sound Reti for White.}) 14. Bg5 $5 (14. cxd5 Nxd5) (14. Nb5 $6 axb5 15. cxb5 Qa5 $1 16. Qb3 e4 (16... Nd4 $4 17. Nxd4 exd4 18. Bf4 $18) (16... Na7 17. a4 $44 {[%csl Ga5,Ga7]}) 17. bxc6 Bxc6 18. Bc2 Nf5 $15) 14... e4 $1 15. cxd5 $1 {A ridiculous engine line, but there is some logic to the whole thing.} (15. Bb1 Qe5 $15 (15... Nd4 16. Qd1 $16)) 15... exd3 16. Nc3 $1 (16. dxc6 Bxc6 17. Qg4+ Bd7 $17) {All Black needs to focus on is coordination over material. Thus} 16... Bg7 (16... Ne5 17. Qf4 {White is down a piece but Black's pieces totally lack coordination.}) 17. Rac1 Kb8 {and White must go for a draw with} 18. Ncb5 axb5 19. Nxb5 Qa5 (19... Qb6 $5 20. dxc6 ({Not} 20. Be3 Qa6 21. Ba7+ Qxa7 $1 $19) 20... Bxc6 $5 (20... Nxc6 21. Be3 $8 Qa5 (21... Qa6 $2 22. Ba7+ $1 Ka8 (22... Kc8 23. Qf4 {mates.}) (22... Nxa7 23. Qf4+ {mates.}) 23. Nc7+ $16) 22. Bf4+ $11) 21. Qf4+ (21. Bf4+ Kc8) 21... Kc8 22. Nd6+ Rxd6 23. Qxd6 Nf5 24. Qxd3 $13) 20. Bf4+ Ka8 21. Nc7+ Kb8 {with a typical engine finish.}) 10... fxe5 11. c4 $4 {Inexplicable blunder from the Armenian number one. Inexplicable blunder from the Armenian number one. GM Davorin Kuljasevic: '?' GM Davorin Kuljasevic: 'A speculative sacrifice that did not work out.'} (11. Qa4 {and Black may as well transpose to the above note.} Bf5 {is possible but unnecessarily risky. For instance is possible but unnecessarily risky. For instance GM Davorin Kuljasevic: '='} 12. Bxf5 Nxf5 (12... gxf5 13. f4 e4 14. Be3 Bg7 15. Na3 $36) 13. c4 d4 14. Nd2) 11... e4 $19 {The rest needs no comment.} 12. Bxe4 dxe4 13. Nbc3 Bg7 14. Nd5 Qd6 15. Bf4 Be5 16. Rad1 Bxf4 17. Ndxf4 Qe5 {GM Davorin Kuljasevic: '-+'} 18. b4 Nxb4 19. Qb3 Nbc6 20. c5 Qxc5 21. Nc3 Qb4 22. Qc2 O-O 23. Ncd5 Nxd5 24. Nxd5 Qa3 25. Rfe1 Bf5 26. Re3 Qa5 27. Qc4 Rf7 28. Nf6+ Kg7 29. Rd5 Be6 0-1


