1. Nf3 d5 2. d4 Nf6 (2... e6 3. c4 c6 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 b5 6. O-O Bb7 7. a4 Nf6 8. Ne5 a6 9. Nc3 {- game}) 3. c4 c6 4. Nc3 e6 5. g3 dxc4 6. Bg2 b5 7. Ne5 a6 8. O-O Bb7 9. a4 Nd5 10. Ne4 (10. axb5 axb5 11. Rxa8 Bxa8 {- see annotations to Romanishin - Goloshchapov}) 10... f6 $1 {This move is quite appropriate when Black's knight has already come out to d5.} (10... Be7 11. Nc5 $5 $44) (10... Nd7 11. Nxf7 $5 Kxf7 12. Ng5+ Ke7 13. e4 Nc7 14. d5 $44 {0-1 Pepic,R (2225)-Bator,R (2502)/Sweden 2003/EXT 2005 (45)}) 11. Nf3 Nd7 12. Bh3 Qe7 13. Bd2 f5 14. Neg5 {Going for a risky piece sacrifice is practically forced.} h6 15. Nxe6 Qxe6 16. e4 Ne7 17. exf5 Qd5 $6 (17... Qf7 $142 {, and Black must parry White's attack, e.g.} 18. Ne5 Nxe5 19. dxe5 Nxf5 20. e6 Qg6 21. Ba5 Nd6 22. Bc7 Be7 $1 23. Bxd6 Rd8) 18. Bg2 Nf6 19. Re1 O-O-O 20. Ba5 Rd7 $2 21. Ne5 Qxd4 22. Nxd7 $2 (22. Qe2 $1 $18 {}) 22... Qxd7 23. axb5 axb5 24. b3 Qxd1 25. Rexd1 Ned5 26. bxc4 bxc4 27. Rdc1 Bd6 28. Rxc4 Kd7 29. Bd2 Re8 30. Bf3 Bc7 31. Kg2 Bb6 32. Ba5 Ra8 33. Rca4 Bc5 34. Bd2 Re8 35. Re1 Rf8 36. Rb1 Kc7 37. g4 Re8 38. Re1 Rf8 39. Rb1 Re8 40. Re1 Rxe1 41. Bxe1 Bd6 42. Bd2 Nd7 43. h4 Ne5 44. Be2 c5 45. Kf1 Nc6 46. g5 hxg5 47. hxg5 Nd4 48. f6 gxf6 49. g6 Nxe2 50. g7 Ne7 51. Kxe2 Bd5 52. Ra7+ Kb6 53. Bf4 Kxa7 54. Bxd6 Ng8 55. Bxc5+ Kb7 56. Ke3 Kc6 57. Bf8 Kd7 58. Kf4 Ke6 0-1


