1. e4 {Marin,M Marin,M Marin,M} e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Nxe4 6. d4 b5 7. Bb3 d5 8. dxe5 Be6 9. Nbd2 Nc5 10. c3 d4 11. Bxe6 Nxe6 12. cxd4 Ncxd4 13. a4 Bb4 14. Nxd4 ({Marin,M: 'The other possibility' The other possibility} 14. axb5 Nxb5 $1 {Marin,M: 'was covered in the notes to Volokitin, A (2671)-Nakamura,H (2660)/Biel 2005/CBM 108/[Mikhalevski,V] (1/2-1/2, 41)' was covered in the notes to Volokitin,A (2671)-Nakamura,H (2660)/Biel 2005/CBM 108/[Mikhalevski,V] (½-½, 41)}) 14... Nxd4 $146 {Marin,M: 'Black makes a curious novely in a variation where things were supposed to be OK for him.' Black makes a curious novely in a variation where things were supposed to be OK for him.} ({Marin,M: 'The temporary pawn sacrifice' The temporary pawn sacrifice} 14... Qxd4 {Marin,M: 'activates the queen and leaves White slightly underdeveloped. "Winning" pawns with' activates the queen and leaves White slightly underdeveloped.} {"Winning" pawns with} 15. axb5 (15. Qc2 O-O 16. Nf3 Qc4 17. Qxc4 bxc4 18. Be3 c3 19. bxc3 Bxc3 20. Rac1 Ba5 {Otero,D (2400)-Alonso,R (2387)/Santa Clara 2005/CBM 105 ext (½-½, 41). Marin,M: 'Otero,D (2400)-Alonso,R (2387)/Santa Clara 2005/CBM 105 ext (1/2-1/2, 41). The e6-knight ensures Black almost absolute stability in the centre.' The e6-knight ensures Black almost absolute stability in the centre.}) (15. Qe2 O-O 16. Nf3 Qd5 (16... Qc4 {Marin,M: 'transposes above.' transposes above.}) 17. Be3 Rfd8 18. Qc2 c5 19. Rfd1 Qc6 20. h3 c4 $132 {Passerotti,P-Thipsay,P (2430)/Lucerne 1982/EXT 97-B (½-½, 26). Marin,M: 'Passerotti,P-Thipsay,P (2430)/Lucerne 1982/EXT 97-B (1/2-1/2, 26). Black has an active queenside position, while the other wing is safely defended by his knight.' Black has an active queenside position, while the other wing is safely defended by his knight.}) 15... O-O 16. bxa6 $6 {Marin,M: 'looks too risky, because of the pin along the d-file.' looks too risky, because of the pin along the d-file.} (16. Nf3 Qxd1 17. Rxd1 axb5 {Djukic,N (2521)-Predojevic,B (2543)/Vrnjacka Banja 2005/EXT 2006 (½-½, 23) Marin,M: 'Djukic,N (2521)-Predojevic,B (2543)/Vrnjacka Banja 2005/EXT 2006 (1/2-1/2, 23)'}) (16. Rxa6 $2 Rad8 17. Qc2 Bxd2 18. Rd1 Bxc1 19. Rxd4 Nxd4 $19 {Predojevic}) (16. Qa4 Bxd2 17. Qxd4 Nxd4 18. Bxd2 Nb3 19. Rad1 axb5 20. Bc3 c5 $36) 16... Rfd8 17. Qf3 (17. Qc2 Bxd2 18. Rd1 Bxc1 $1 19. Rxd4 Nxd4 20. Qxc7 Bxb2 $17) 17... Bxd2 18. Rd1 Bxc1 19. Rxd4 Nxd4 20. Qb7 {Navara,D (2646)-Hracek,Z (2581)/Czechia 2005/EXT 2007 (½-½, 36) Marin,M: 'Navara,D (2646)-Hracek,Z (2581)/ Czechia 2005/EXT 2007 (1/2-1/2, 36)'} Ra7 $3 21. Qxa7 Nc6 {[%cal Yd8d1]} 22. Rxc1 Nxa7 $17) 15. Nf3 (15. axb5 {Marin,M: 'could lead to similar positions after' could lead to similar positions after} a5 (15... axb5 $5 16. Rxa8 Qxa8 17. Qg4 $16 {[%csl Yd4,Yg7]}) 16. Nb3 (16. Nf3 {Marin,M: 'transposes to the game.' transposes to the game.}) 16... Nxb3 17. Qxb3 O-O 18. Rd1 Qe8 {Marin,M: 'The white queen is probably better placed on f3, because it keeps the a8-rook and the f7-square under pressure at the same time.' The white queen is probably better placed on f3, because it keeps the a8-rook and the f7-square under pressure at the same time.}) 15... Nxf3+ 16. Qxf3 O-O 17. axb5 a5 {Marin,M: 'Black consolidates his bishop and hopes to obtain compensation on light squares.' Black consolidates his bishop and hopes to obtain compensation on light squares.} ({Marin,M: 'However, I wonder whether Black had intended to play that from the beginning or whether he simply noticed too late that' However, I wonder whether Black had intended to play that from the beginning or whether he simply noticed too late that} 17... axb5 $2 {Marin,M: 'loses to' loses to} 18. Rxa8 Qxa8 19. Qg4 c5 20. Bh6 $18) 18. Rd1 Qe8 19. Rd5 c6 20. bxc6 Qxc6 21. Be3 (21. Bf4 Qc2 22. b3 $14 {Marin,M: 'offered White chances to consolidate his material advantage.' offered White chances to consolidate his material advantage.}) 21... Qc2 22. Qd1 $6 (22. Bd4 Rad8 $44) (22. Rd7 $1 {[%csl Ga8][%cal Yd7f7]} Rad8 23. Qd1 $1 $14 {Marin,M: 'maintains White's minimal material advantage.' maintains White's minimal material advantage.}) 22... Qxb2 23. Bd4 Bc3 $11 24. Rb1 Qd2 25. Qxd2 Bxd2 26. Kf1 Rfd8 27. Rxd8+ Rxd8 28. Rb7 f6 29. Bb6 Re8 30. Bc7 Bc3 31. Ra7 Bxe5 1/2-1/2


