1. d4 {Sumets,Andrey Sumets,Andrey Sumets,Andrey} Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Nf3 Bg7 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. e3 O-O 7. Bc4 Nb6 8. Bb3 c5 9. O-O Bg4 {A rare sideline. A rare sideline. Sumets,Andrey: '?!' '?!' '?!' Sumets,Andrey: 'Black's idea is not to open the diagonal c1-h6. Compared to the line 9...cxd4 10.exd4 g4 White has less space. However, 9...g4 seems to be a dubious move, because of its tactical drawbacks.' Sumets,Andrey: 'Black's idea is not to open the diagonal c1-h6. Compared to the line 9...cxd4 10.exd4 g4 White has less space. However, 9...g4 seems to be a dubious move, because of its tactical drawbacks. '} ({Mamedyarov had success with the novelty} 9... c4 10. Bc2 Nc6 11. Qe2 ({but I would prefer} 11. h3 {here and if} e5 12. d5 Nb4 13. e4) 11... Bg4) (9... cxd4 10. exd4 {is the main line.}) 10. dxc5 {Sumets,Andrey: '!' '!' '!' Sumets,Andrey: 'White's only chance to get an edge.' Sumets,Andrey: 'White's only chance to get an edge.'} N6d7 11. h3 (11. e4 $5 Nxc5 $2 12. Bxf7+ $1 Kxf7 13. Ng5+) 11... Bxf3 12. Qxf3 Nxc5 13. Rd1 Qc8 14. Nd5 {Sumets,Andrey: 'I believe this is a promising try for getting an advantage. It is more important to gain space in the centre than to keep the bishop pair. The white knight on d5 is very well placed.' Sumets,Andrey: 'I believe this is a promising try for getting an advantage. It is more important to gain space in the centre than to keep the bishop pair. The white knight on d5 is very well placed.'} (14. Bc2 {Sumets,Andrey} Nc6 15. a3 Qe6 16. Rb1 Rad8 17. Bd2 Nd3 $6 (17... Ne5 $5 18. Qe2 Nc4 19. Be1 Rxd1 20. Bxd1 Rc8 $132) 18. Qe2 Nde5 19. Be1 Qc4 20. Kf1 Rxd1 21. Rxd1 Rd8 22. Rxd8+ Nxd8 23. b3 Qxe2+ 24. Kxe2 $14 {1-0 Tregubov, P-Khalifman,A Novokuznetsk 2008 (76)}) 14... Nc6 15. e4 {White should be a little better even though Black's bishop on g7 is a fine piece.} Re8 {Sumets,Andrey: '?!' '?!' '?!' Sumets,Andrey: 'I think this move is the cause of further problems for Black.' Sumets,Andrey: 'I think this move is the cause of further problems for Black.'} (15... e6 16. Nf6+ Bxf6 17. Qxf6 Nxe4 18. Qh4 Nc5 19. Bh6 {is too strong but removing White's bishop pair looks reasonable}) (15... Nxb3 {Sumets,Andrey: '!' '!' '!'} 16. axb3 (16. Qxb3 {Sumets,Andrey} e6) 16... f5 $5 (16... Re8 {Sumets,Andrey} 17. Be3 Bxb2 18. Rab1 Be5 19. b4 $44 {Sumets,Andrey: 'White has good compensation for the pawn.' White has good compensation for the pawn.})) 16. Bg5 Ne6 (16... Bxb2 {Sumets,Andrey Sumets,Andrey: 'is a very risky but an interesting attempt' is a very risky but an interesting attempt} 17. Rab1 Be5 18. Rdc1 $1 (18. Nxe7+ $6 Rxe7 19. Bxe7 Nxb3 20. Qxb3 Nxe7 21. Qxb7 Nc6 22. Qxc8+ Rxc8 23. Rbc1 Kf8 24. Rd7 Rd8 $11) 18... Nxb3 (18... Bd6 19. Nb6 Ne5 (19... axb6 $4 20. Qxf7+ Kh8 21. Qf6+ exf6 22. Bxf6#) 20. Bxf7+ Kg7 (20... Kh8 $4 21. Qf6+) 21. Bh6+ $1 Kh8 22. Nxc8 Nxf3+ 23. gxf3 Rexc8 24. Bd5 $16) 19. Qxb3 Qe6 20. Qxb7 Nd4 21. Rd1 f6 22. Be3 Ne2+ 23. Kf1 Nc3 24. Nxc3 Bxc3 25. Qb3 $14) 17. Bh4 Qb8 (17... Bxb2 18. Rab1 Be5 19. Ba4 $1 {puts Black under pressure. puts Black under pressure. Sumets,Andrey: '' '' ''}) 18. Rac1 Qe5 19. Rxc6 $1 {Sumets,Andrey: '!' '!' '!'} bxc6 20. Nxe7+ Kh8 (20... Rxe7 21. Bxe7 Qxb2 22. Rd7 Qc1+ 23. Kh2 Be5+ 24. g3) 21. Nxc6 Qxb2 22. e5 $1 {All White’s pieces are active and Black has to make too many concessions to defend the f7 pawn.} Rec8 (22... Rf8 23. Be7) 23. Bf6 $1 ({stronger than} 23. Qxf7 Rxc6 24. Bf6 Rc1 $1) 23... Rc7 24. Bxe6 fxe6 25. Nd8 $1 Bxf6 26. Qxa8 (26. exf6 {also wins.}) 26... Qc2 27. Nf7+ 1-0


