sen was clearly the favourite in this game and his knight retreat reveals his honest ambitions. From g6 the knight eyes the weak spots f4 and h4. Carlsen was clearly the favourite in this game and his knight retreat reveals his honest ambitions. From g6 the knight eyes the weak spots f4 and h4. RR: 'Ftacnik: 'Carlsen was clearly the favourite in this game and his knight retreat reveals his honest ambitions. From g6 the knight eyes the weak spots f4 and h4. ''} (13... b5 {RR: 'Ü 110/(109)' RR: 'Ü 110/(109)'} 14. a4 bxa4 15. Nxa4 Bb7 16. Nb6 Rb8 17. Bxe5 {½-½ Svidler,P (2731)-Ivanisevic,I (2613)/Khanty Mansiysk 2010 ½-½ Svidler,P (2731)-Ivanisevic,I (2613)/Khanty Mansiysk 2010}) 14. Be3 (14. f4 $6 Nxf4 15. Rxf4 e5 $15) (14. Na4 Bg5 15. Qb4 a5 16. Qb5 Bd7 $11) 14... Qc7 15. Ne2 (15. Na4 b5 16. Nb6 Rb8 17. Nxc8 Rfxc8 18. Rac1 b4 $15) 15... b5 16. c4 $1 {RR: 'Ftacnik: '!'' Howell is a up and coming player from England with an active approach to the game. He may not get very far on the kingside, but is smart enough to play also on the opposite flank. Howell is a up and coming player from England with an active approach to the game. He may not get very far on the kingside, but is smart enough to play also on the opposite flank. RR: 'Ftacnik: 'Howell is a up and coming player from England with an active approach to the game. He may not get very far on the kingside, but is smart enough to play also on the opposite flank.''} bxc4 (16... Bb7 17. Rac1 Qd7 18. Nf4 Rac8 $11) 17. Rac1 Bb7 18. Rxc4 Qd7 19. Rfc1 Rac8 {RR: '=' '='} 20. Bb6 {Quite naturally the position is about equal and White is working on forcing the exchanges of majory pieces along the c-file. Quite naturally the position is about equal and White is working on forcing the exchanges of majory pieces along the c-file.} (20. Nd4 h6 21. Qa5 Rxc4 22. Rxc4 Rc8 $11) 20... Rxc4 21. Rxc4 Rc8 22. Qc2 Rxc4 23. Qxc4 (23. bxc4 $2 Qc6 $15) 23... Qe8 $5 {Black knows very well that he can not exchange queens and hope for the advantage. Black knows very well that he can not exchange queens and hope for the advantage.} 24. a4 (24. Qc7 Qa8 25. Ng3 h6 26. Bd4 Bc6 $11) 24... Qa8 25. f4 $6 {White is less experienced than his opponent who is sitting on the top of world rating list. Exposing the structure and his own king on the kingside brings no benefit and is dangerous. White is less experienced than his opponent who is sitting on the top of world rating list. Exposing the structure and his own king on the kingside brings no benefit and is dangerous.} (25. Ba5 Bc6 26. Qd3 h6 27. Bd2 $11) 25... h6 26. Bf2 Bh4 27. Be3 (27. Bxh4 Nxh4 28. Bh1 Qd8 29. b4 Ng6 $15) 27... Bf6 28. Qd3 (28. Ng3 Nh4 29. Bh1 d5 30. Qd3 (30. exd5 Bxd5 31. Bxd5 exd5 32. Qe2 d4 $17) 30... dxe4 31. Bxe4 Bxe4 32. Nxe4 Be7 33. Bf2 Qb7 $15) 28... Bc6 29. Ng3 (29. g5 hxg5 30. fxg5 Be5 $15) 29... Be7 {The positions has become more pleasant for Black, but making progress is another story. The positions has become more pleasant for Black, but making progress is another story.} 30. Nh5 Bf8 31. Bf2 Qb7 32. Qc4 (32. Kh2 e5 (32... Ne7 33. Bd4 d5 34. Qc3 f6 35. g5 $13) 33. f5 Nf4 34. Nxf4 exf4 35. Be1 Be7 36. Bd2 Bg5 37. Qf3 Qb6 38. Bxf4 Bxf4+ 39. Qxf4 Qxb3 40. Qxd6 Qxa4 41. f6 $11) 32... Ne7 33. Qd3 d5 $5 {Both players have understood, that the position will have to be opened at some stage. Both players have understood, that the position will have to be opened at some stage.} 34. e5 (34. exd5 Bxd5 35. Bxd5 Nxd5 $15) 34... d4 (34... Bd7 35. Bf1 Nc6 36. Be2 $11) 35. Bf1 (35. Bxc6 Nxc6 36. Ng3 a5 37. Ne4 Qd7 $15) 35... Bd5 36. Qxa6 $6 {Howell must have been excited by the prospect of eliminating all the queenside pawns. His choice of move keepis the flame of battle burning. Howell must have been excited by the prospect of eliminating all the queenside pawns. His choice of move keepis the flame of battle burning.} (36. Bxd4 $1 Bxb3 37. Qxa6 Qb4 38. Bf2 Bxa4 39. Qc4 $11) 36... Qxb3 37. Qd3 (37. Bxd4 Nc6 38. Bb6 Be7 $17) 37... Qxa4 38. Qxd4 Qa8 39. Qa7 Qc8 40. Qc5 (40. Qa3 Ng6 41. Qb2 Be7 42. Bg2 $15) 40... Nc6 41. Qc3 Qa8 {Baburin (www.chesstoday.net): 'Diagram  Both armies are the same and pawns are on the same flank, but Black's chances are better as the white king is a bit exposed and his pawns (f4 and potentially e5) are vulnerable.'} 42. g5 $2 {[%mdl 256] Baburin (www.chesstoday.net): '?!' White had to think hard about the best way of defending his exposed pawn structure. He decides to lash out into counterplay, but does it at the wrong moment. White had to think hard about the best way of defending his exposed pawn structure. He decides to lash out into counterplay, but does it at the wrong moment.} (42. Bc4 Nb4 43. Bxd5 Qxd5 44. Kh2 Nd3 $15) (42. Bd3 Bb4 43. Qb2 Be7 $15) (42. Ng3 {Baburin (www.chesstoday.net)} Bb4 43. Qd3 Qa1) (42. f5 {Baburin (www.chesstoday.net)} Qa2) 42... Qa4 $1 (42... hxg5 43. fxg5 Qa2 44. Nf4 Bb4 45. Qg3 Nxe5 $17) 43. Qg3 {Baburin (www.chesstoday.net): '?'} (43. gxh6 Qe4 44. Ng3 Qxf4 45. hxg7 Bxg7 $17) 43... Qd1 {Baburin (www.chesstoday.net): '!' Two precise moves have managed to prove that White has lost the battle. The hanging knight on h5 can not be sensibly defended. Two precise moves have managed to prove that White has lost the battle. The hanging knight on h5 can not be sensibly defended.} 44. Nf6+ (44. Qh4 Bc4 45. Ng3 Nd4 46. Qg4 Nf3+ 47. Kg2 Bd5 $19) 44... gxf6 45. gxf6+ Kh8 46. Qd3 {After the act of desperation, reality refuses to run away. Due to the pin along the first rank White has to swap the queens. After the act of desperation, reality refuses to run away. Due to the pin along the first rank White has to swap the queens.} Qxd3 47. Bxd3 {Baburin (www.chesstoday.net): 'Diagram  The black king is out of play, but that's a temporary factor.'} Nb4 48. Bb1 (48. Bf1 Kh7 49. Be3 Kg6 $19) 48... Ba2 49. Be4 Nd5 50. f5 {The game is clearly over. White can not even dream about holding the game with only a pawn for the piece. The game is clearly over. White can not even dream about holding the game with only a pawn for the piece.} (50. Bg3 Bc5+ 51. Kg2 Bc4 52. Kf3 Nc3 53. Bc2 h5 $19) 50... Nf4 51. Kh2 exf5 52. Bxf5 Be6 53. Bg4 (53. Bb1 Nxh3 $19) 53... Bxg4 54. hxg4 Ne6 55. Kg3 Bc5 {RR: '0-1 (55) Howell,D (2611)-Carlsen,M (2802) London 2010 CBM 140 [Ftacnik]'} 0-1


