f course Black also continues the development.} 11. Nb5 O-O 12. Nxc7 Rb8 13. Qb5 {Szabo,Kr: 'A tempting reaction. The queen stops ...b5, however this is not the best square for it.' A tempting reaction. The queen stops ...b5, however this is not the best square for it.} (13. Kb1 {Szabo,Kr: 'would be more solid, but' would be more solid, but} Bf5 $36 {Szabo,Kr: 'is also unpleasant for White.' is also unpleasant for White.}) 13... Bd7 $6 {Szabo,Kr: 'A natural reply, but it wasn't the best.' A natural reply, but it wasn't the best.} (13... Rd8 $1 {Szabo,Kr: 'was correct and suddenly White is in trouble, for example:' was correct and suddenly White is in trouble, for example:} 14. Rxd8+ Bxd8 15. Nd5 Nxd5 16. Qxd5 exf3 17. gxf3 (17. Qxf3 Nb4 $19 {Szabo,Kr: 'and Black is winning.' and Black is winning.}) 17... Qxc2+ $1 {Szabo,Kr: 'A smart solution!' A smart solution!} 18. Kxc2 Nb4+ $17 {Szabo,Kr: 'and Black will be a healthy pawn up in the endgame.' and Black will be a healthy pawn up in the endgame.}) 14. Nc5 Nd4 15. Qb6 $6 {Szabo,Kr: 'A dubious move, because White should protect the important c2-square.' A dubious move, because White should protect the important c2-square.} ({Szabo,Kr: 'White should have played' White should have played} 15. Qc4 Nf5 ({or} 15... Bxc5 16. Qxc5 {transposing to the game.}) 16. Bf4 Bc6 $132 {Szabo,Kr: 'with a double-edged fight.' with a double-edged fight.}) 15... Bxc5 $6 {Szabo,Kr: 'Error in reply!' Error in reply!} (15... Nxc2 $1 {Szabo,Kr: 'was the tactical blow,' was the tactical blow,} 16. Nxd7 ({Szabo,Kr: 'or' or} 16. Kxc2 exf3+ 17. Bd3 Bf5 18. gxf3 Rfd8 $17 {Szabo,Kr: 'and White is in trouble.' and White is in trouble.}) 16... Nxe3 17. Qxe3 Nxd7 18. Qxe4 Qxe4 19. fxe4 Nc5 $15 {Szabo,Kr: 'and Black looks nicely placed.' and Black looks nicely placed.}) 16. Qxc5 {Szabo,Kr: 'transposing to the game.' Szabo,Kr: 'transposing to the game.'} Ne6 17. Nxe6 Bxe6 18. Qg5 $1 {Szabo,Kr: 'A good move, White simplifies the position. Now Black has to be careful, otherwise with the bishop pair White can play for the advantage.' A good move, White simplifies the position. Now Black has to be careful, otherwise with the bishop pair White can play for the advantage.} exf3 19. gxf3 Rfc8 20. Qxg6 (20. Bd3 {Szabo,Kr: 'was the alternative,' was the alternative,} Qxg5 21. Bxg5 Bxa2 22. Rhg1 $44 {Szabo,Kr: 'with compensation for the pawn.' with compensation for the pawn.} ({Szabo,Kr: 'But not' But not} 22. b3 $2 {Szabo,Kr: ', because of' , because of} Bxb3 $17)) 20... hxg6 21. a3 b5 22. Bd4 b4 23. axb4 axb4 24. Bd3 Nd7 (24... Ra8 $5 {Szabo,Kr: 'was the other logical option.' was the other logical option.}) 25. Rhe1 Rc6 $6 {Szabo,Kr: 'Black would like to activate his R, but probably this was not the best moment for it.' Black would like to activate his , but probably this was not the best moment for it.} ({Szabo,Kr: 'The engine suggests' The engine suggests} 25... g5 {Szabo,Kr: 'to gain some space and play move by move on the kingside.' to gain some space and play move by move on the kingside.}) 26. Be4 Ra6 27. b3 Nf6 28. Be5 Re8 29. Bd3 Ra5 30. Kb2 Nd5 31. Bc4 Rea8 32. Bxd5 $6 {Szabo,Kr: 'This is a surprise for me to give up the bishop pair with White and play an opposite-coloured bishop endgame.' This is a surprise for me to give up the bishop pair with White and play an opposite-coloured bishop endgame.} ({Szabo,Kr: 'I think after' I think after} 32. Ra1 $1 {Szabo,Kr: 'White has a slight edge, for example:' White has a slight edge, for example:} Ra3 (32... Rxa1 33. Rxa1 Rxa1 34. Kxa1 $14) 33. Bd6 $1 $14 {Szabo,Kr: 'and Black's position is not easy.' and Black's position is not easy.}) 32... Bxd5 {Szabo,Kr: 'And the draw was agreed!' And the draw was agreed!} 1/2-1/2


