nation of his forces, or weaken his position.'} ({He chooses the latter,} 12... Re8 {Stohl,Igor} 13. d6 $1 {gives White attacking chances with the dangerous -wedge on d6. However, perhaps even this is playable after} Nd7 $5 {- see Pashikian-Zhou Jiangchao.}) 13. Be3 {Stohl,Igor: '!?' Probably the most solid reply. Stohl,Igor: 'The latest wrinkle, the  returns back after forcing the ugly f6.'} ({Stohl,Igor: 'Only a year ago the main move was'} 13. Bf4 {has been played in some recent games:} {Stohl,Igor: 'Then Black came up with'} Qa4 {Stohl,Igor: '!'} (13... exd5 14. exd5 Bf5 15. Be2 Be4 16. d6 Nd7 17. h4 h5 18. O-O Qa4 19. Rfe1 Kh7 20. Bb5 $1 Qxb5 21. Rxe4 $16 {1-0 Potkin,V (2626)-Zhou Jianchao (2668)/Ningbo 2010/CBM 138 (28)}) (13... f5 $2 {Stohl,Igor} 14. Bc4 Qa4 15. Qe2 b5 16. Bxb5 Qxe4 17. dxe6 $1 Bxe6 18. Ng5 Qxe2+ 19. Kxe2 Bxa2 20. Ra1 Bf7 21. Rhd1 Rc8 22. Nxf7 Kxf7 23. Bc4+ Ke8 24. Be6 $18 {Giri,A (2588)-Howell,D (2606)/Wijk aan Zee/2010/}) (13... Nc6 {Stohl,Igor} 14. Bc4 b5 15. Be2 g5 16. Bg3 exd5 17. exd5 Ne7 $6 ({Nobody was yet willing to risk} 17... g4 $5 18. Nh4 Be6 19. Qe3 Bxd5 20. O-O $44) 18. d6 Bb7 19. Qc2 Ng6 20. O-O $16 {Jakovenko,D (2725)-Ponomariov,R (2733)/Astrakhan/2010/}) 14. c4 (14. Qc2 Qxc2 15. Rxc2 exd5 (15... Re8 $5 {Stohl,Igor} 16. Bc4 Nd7 17. dxe6 Nb6 18. Bd5 Bxe6 19. Bxb7 Rad8 $44) 16. exd5 Bf5 17. Rb2 Be4 18. c4 {Stohl,Igor: '!?'} (18. Bc4 {Stohl,Igor} Nd7 $5 (18... Bxd5 19. Bxd5+ Rxd5 20. Rxb7 Nc6 21. O-O (21. Rc7 Nd8 $1 22. Re7 Bf8 23. Re2 Kf7 24. Rd2 Rxd2 25. Kxd2 Ne6 $11) 21... Nd8 $5 (21... Rc8 22. h3 f5 $132) 22. Re7 Bf8 23. Re8 Kf7 24. Rfe1 Rd7 $11 {Arsovic}) 19. Nd2 Bxg2 20. Rg1 Bh3 21. Rg3 Bf5 22. Rxb7 Nb6 23. d6+ Nxc4 24. Nxc4 g5 25. h4 h6 26. Re7 Rd7 27. hxg5 hxg5 28. Bxg5 fxg5 29. Rxg5 Rxe7+ 30. dxe7 Re8 $11 {Ding,L (2565)-Gupta,A (2560)/Olongapo City/2010/}) 18... Bxf3 19. gxf3 b6 20. Re2 Na6 21. a3 Kf7 22. h4 h5 23. Kd2 Re8 $11 {1/2 Ragger,M (2614)-Bosiocic,M (2562)/Chur 2010/CBM 136 Extra (47)} 24. Rxe8 {Stohl,Igor} Rx