its his d7, I think Black still should have played} 19... f5 $142 $5 {Stohl,Igor} 20. Nc3 Nc7 $14 {and White's edge is less distinct, than it was in the game.} (20... Bd4 $5)) 20. Nc3 (20. Ng3 {Stohl,Igor} Bd7 {wins a tempo, but misplaces the .}) 20... Nb4 (20... Nc7 {Stohl,Igor} 21. h5 Ne8 22. g4 $5 (22. Kd2 Nd6 23. hxg6 hxg6 24. Bd3 $14 {/}) 22... Bc8 23. hxg6 hxg6 24. Ne4 $36) 21. Kd2 {Stohl,Igor: ''} Nc6 {The knight enters the game a bit too late.} 22. h5 (22. g4 {Stohl,Igor is roughly equivalent.}) 22... Kf7 {Hardly a useful move. Stohl,Igor: 'The  is not ideally placed here and will have to go back soon.'} (22... Ne5 $142 {Stohl,Igor: '!?'} 23. f3 {Stohl,Igor} Re8) 23. g4 Bc8 24. hxg6+ (24. Ne4 $5 {Stohl,Igor is perhaps more flexible, White retains the option to play h6.}) 24... hxg6 25. Ne4 Ba6 {Stohl,Igor: 'The  will remain offside till the end of the game, but it's not simple to suggest anything better.'} (25... Ne5 $142 26. f3 $16 {Stohl,Igor: ''} (26. Bf4 $1 {Stohl,Igor} Nxg4 27. Bc7 $44)) 26. Rh7 $1 {Stohl,Igor: '!?' Stohl,Igor: 'h6'} (26. Bf4 $1 {Stohl,Igor prevents e5 and threatens d6, after} Nd4 27. Bd3 Kg8 28. Rh3 Bc8 29. Rg1 $16 {Black's  is under strong pressure.}) 26... Kg8 27. Rch1 $1 (27. Rh3 $5 $36 {Stohl,Igor}) 27... Ne5 {Stohl,Igor: '×c4 is the main drawback of White's previous move.'} (27... Nd4 $6 {Stohl,Igor} 28. Bxd4 cxd4 29. g5 fxg5 30. Nxg5 Bc8 31. Bd3 $40) (27... Na5 {Stohl,Igor} 28. g5 $1 (28. Kc3 $36 {} f5+ $2 29. Rxg7+ Kxg7 30. gxf5 gxf5 31. Rg1+ Kh8 32. Nf6 $18) 28... fxg5 29. Bxg5 Rf8 30. Rxg7+ Kxg7 31. Bh6+ Kg8 32. Bxf8 Rxf8 33. Rc1 (33. Kc3 $6 Rf4 $14 (33... Bxc4 $5 34. Bxc4 Rf3+ $14)) 33... Rf4 34. f3 $16 {[%csl Ra5,Ra6,Gc4] The c4 is protected and Black's minor pieces are offside.}) 28. Kc3 $2 {Allowing a tactical trick.} (28. g5 $1 fxg5 29. Bxg5 Rf8 $8 (29... Nxc4+ $2 {Stohl,Igor} 30. Bxc4 Bxc4 31. Nf6+ Bxf6 (31... Kf8 32. Rxg7 $18) 32. Bxf6 Rxd5+ 33. Kc3 $18) 30. Kc3 $1 $16 {leads to the game position.}) 28...