ve Black loses material without sufficient compensation. It was better to give up the exchange keeping his c-pawn and moving it to c2:} (21... Qd7 $1 22. Rb5 c2 $1 23. Nd2 $1 Bd3 $1 24. Rb3 Bf5 25. Bxc8 Rxc8 $44 {[%cal Yg7h6]} 26. e4 $2 Bh6) 22. Rb5 Rcd8 $6 (22... e6 23. Bxc8 Rxc8 24. Ne5 $16) 23. Ne5 (23. Bh4 $1 {[%cal Yf3g5] was even stronger, e.g.} Qe6 (23... Qf5 24. Bxe7) 24. Ng5 Qg4 25. Nxe4 Qxe4 26. Bxe7 Qxe7 27. Bxd5 $18) 23... a6 24. Rc5 Qb6 25. Bxd5 Bxd5 26. Qxc3 Bxe5 27. Bxe5 {With a pawn up and a superior position, White slowly but steadily wins:} Qb3 28. Qa5 f6 29. Bg3 Bb7 30. Rc7 Rc8 31. h3 Rxc7 32. Rxc7 Re8 33. Qc5 Qd5 34. f3 Qxc5 35. dxc5 Bd5 36. Ra7 Rc8 37. e4 Bb3 38. Bf2 Bxa4 39. Rxe7 Bb5 40. Bd4 Rf8 41. Rc7 a5 (41... Rf7 42. Rc8+ Rf8 43. Rxf8+ Kxf8 44. Bxf6 $18 {}) 42. Rb7 Be8 43. Rb6 f5 44. exf5 gxf5 45. c6 Kf7 46. Bc5 Rg8 47. Rb7+ Ke6 48. Rb8 Bf7 49. c7 Kd7 50. Bb6 Rc8 51. Bxa5 Be6 52. Kf2 1-0


