1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. Bxc6 bxc6 5. O-O Bg7 6. Re1 Nh6 7. d4 $6 {This move is illogical. It's main drawback is, that white exchanges his central  to one of black's double pawns. The advantages of this move are much less clear.} ({The main line is} 7. c3 { to create a pawncentre after d2-d4.}) 7... cxd4 8. Nxd4 O-O 9. c4 $146 (9. Nc3 f6 10. h3 Nf7 11. b3 e5 12. Nde2 d6 13. Ng3 Re8 14. Bb2 Be6 15. Qd3 Qa5 16. Na4 d5 17. Rad1 Rad8 $132 {½-½ Xu Yuhua-Kovalevskaya,E/Shanghai 2001/EXT 2002 (72)}) (9. e5 c5 10. Nb3 d6 11. Nc3 Nf5 12. Bf4 Bb7 13. Qe2 Qb6 14. Rad1 Qb4 $15 {0-1 Montheard,X-Degraeve,J/Montpellier 1999/EXT 2001 (26)}) 9... Qb6 10. Nb3 d6 11. c5 $6 {This is too ambitious. White is trying to seize the initiative in a position which already requires accurate play, in order not to get a worse position.} (11. Be3 $11) 11... dxc5 12. Qc2 $2 (12. N1d2 Ng4 {[%csl Rf2]} 13. Nc4 Qc7 14. e5 $15) 12... c4 $1 {[%mdl 128] An excellent decision, based on concrete considerations, which actually refutes white's idea. From now on, every black move will contain a threat...} 13. Qxc4 Ng4 14. Qc2 $6 (14. Qe2 Qc7 15. g3 {white's position is still holding together, since his  is taking part in the defense, which is not the case with the  on c2.} Ne5 16. Bf4) 14... Qc7 {Forcing white to weaken the white squares around the g1.} 15. g3 {[%csl Rf3,Rh3]} Ne5 16. Kg2 $2 {The inexperienced English junior does not have a good sense of danger.} (16. Bf4 $2 Nf3+ 17. Kh1 Nxe1 {[%csl Rc2]}) (16. N1d2 {was the only reasonable move.}) {[%tqu "En","Find the best move for black.","","","c7d7","",5,"c8g4","",0]} 16... Qd7 $1 $19 {[%csl Rh3][%cal Gd7h3]} ({Much weaker is} 16... Bg4 $2 17. f4) 17. N1d2 Qh3+ 18. Kg1 Ba6 {[%csl Rd3] White hasn't even completed his development and has already found himself under a devastating attack.} 19. f4 (19. Nc5 Rad8 $1 $19 {[%csl Rf3][%cal Gd8d2] or 19...fd8!}) (19. f3 Rfd8 $19) 19... Nd3 (19... Bd3 20. Qd1 Ng4 21. Nf3 Rfd8 $19) 20. Re3 $6 (20. Rd1 {would be more stubborn.}) 20... Rad8 {This is also good, but after 20...f4 black could force immediate resignation.} (20... Nxf4 $1 {[%csl Re3,Rf1,Rg2]}) 21. Nf3 Nxf4 $1 {[%csl Rf1]} 22. Re1 Nd3 23. Bg5 Nxe1 24. Rxe1 Rd3 {Materially black is far ahead with a continuing initiative.} 25. Qxc6 Rxf3 26. Qxa6 Rxg3+ 27. hxg3 Qxg3+ 28. Kf1 Qxg5 {The rest of the game is an agony.} 29. Qxa7 Bxb2 30. Re2 Rd8 31. Rxb2 {Of course there was no defense, but now the mate in a few moves follows...} Rd1+ 32. Ke2 Qg4+ 33. Ke3 Qg3+ 34. Ke2 Qd3+ 35. Kf2 Rf1+ 0-1


