1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 dxc4 5. a4 e6 6. e3 c5 7. Bxc4 Nc6 8. O-O cxd4 9. Nxd4 Bd7 10. e4 Nxd4 11. Qxd4 Bc6 12. Qe3 a6 {This is technically a novelty but this position was reached once before with a different move order between some not-as-yet-famous players.} 13. Rd1 (13. e5 {Good or bad this had to be played.} Nd7 14. Qg3 {The starting point of this whole 12...a6 line} g6 $1 (14... Qa5 15. Re1 Bb4 16. Bf1 O-O-O 17. Bg5 f6 18. Be3 Nxe5 19. Rec1 $40) 15. Re1 {We can try and play like Li Chao} (15. Bf4 Qa5 (15... Bg7 16. b4 $1 {Black should always watch out for this move} Nb6 17. Rfd1 Qe7 18. b5 axb5 19. Bxb5 $1 O-O 20. Bxc6 bxc6 21. a5 Nd5 22. Nxd5 exd5 23. a6 {White is slightly better although the draw remains a big favourite here}) 16. Rfe1 Bg7 17. h4 (17. Ne4 Bxe4 18. Rxe4 O-O 19. Be2 Rac8 {[%csl Rd5][%cal Gd7b6,Gb6d5,Ga5c7] Black is completely okay here}) 17... O-O 18. h5 Rfc8 $132) 15... Bg7 16. Bf4 O-O 17. b4 b5 $1 {A typical break in these kinds of position} 18. axb5 axb5 19. Rxa8 Qxa8 20. Bxb5 Bxb5 21. Nxb5 Qb8 22. Nd6 Qxb4 $11) (13. Qe2 {This would transpose to the line which was analysed in the Ragger-Danin game}) 13... Qc7 (13... Nd7 {I somehow thought this was forced which was obviously my stupidity} 14. e5) 14. Qe2 (14. Bd5 {Looks pretty but doesn't achieve anything} O-O-O (14... Ng4 15. Bxc6+ bxc6 16. Qf4 Qxf4 17. Bxf4 Bc5 18. Rd2 Rd8 19. Rc2 $14) (14... Be7 15. Bxc6+ Qxc6 16. e5) 15. Bxc6 Rxd1+ 16. Nxd1 Qxc6 17. Nc3 Bb4 (17... Bd6) 18. Bd2 Rd8 19. Rc1 Kb8 20. Be1 Bxc3 21. Bxc3 Qxa4 22. f3 Rd1+ 23. Kf2 Rxc1 24. Qxc1 Qd7 {should be around =}) (14. Qh3) 14... Qe5 15. f4 Bc5+ 16. Kf1 Qh5 17. Qxh5 Nxh5 18. Ke2 (18. Be2 Nf6 19. Bf3 Nd7 $1 $11) 18... Bb4 19. Bd3 O-O-O 20. Be3 Bxc3 21. bxc3 Nf6 {Already Black is slightly better} 22. e5 Nd5 23. Bd2 Nb6 24. Bc2 h5 (24... Bxg2 25. Be3 Nd5 26. Rg1 Nxc3+ 27. Kf2 Bc6 (27... Be4 28. Ra3 $1) 28. Rxg7 Rd7 29. f5 {White has enough compensation to get a draw here}) 25. Kf2 g6 26. a5 Nc4 27. Bc1 Rxd1 28. Bxd1 Rd8 29. Be2 Nd2 30. Ra3 Nb1 31. Rb3 Nd2 32. Ra3 Nb1 33. Rb3 Nd2 34. Ra3 1/2-1/2


