1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 O-O 8. a4 b4 9. d4 d6 10. dxe5 dxe5 (10... Nxe5 11. Nxe5 dxe5 12. Qe2 (12. Qxd8 Rxd8 13. Nd2 Bc5 14. Nf3 Ng4 15. Be3 Bxe3 16. fxe3 Be6 17. Bxe6 fxe6 18. h3 Nf6 19. Rad1 Rd6 20. Nxe5 Rad8 21. Rd3 Nxe4 22. Rd4) 12... Bc5 13. Be3 Bd4 (13... Qe7 14. Nd2 Bg4 15. Bxc5 Qxc5 16. Qe3 Qxe3 17. Rxe3 Rad8 18. Nc4 Rfe8 19. Na5) 14. c3 bxc3 15. bxc3 Bxe3 16. Qxe3 Qe7 17. Nd2 Be6 18. Bxe6 Qxe6 19. Qc5 Nd7 20. Qxc7 Rac8 21. Qa5 Nc5) 11. Nbd2 Bc5 12. a5 (12. Qe2 Bg4 13. h3 Bh5 14. c3 Na5 15. g4 Bg6) (12. h3 Bb7 13. c3 Qd6 14. Nc4 Qxd1 15. Bxd1 Rad8 16. Bc2 Nd7 17. a5 f6) 12... Be6 13. Qe2 (13. Bxe6 fxe6 14. h3 (14. Nb3 Qxd1 15. Rxd1 Nxe4) (14. Qe2 Ng4 15. Rf1 Nd4) 14... Nh5) 13... Qe7 14. Bxe6 $146 Qxe6 (14... fxe6 15. Nb3) 15. Nb3 Nd4 16. Nfxd4 (16. Nbxd4 Bxd4 17. c3 bxc3 (17... Bc5 18. Bd2 bxc3 19. Bxc3) 18. Nxd4 exd4 19. bxc3 dxc3 20. Ra3 Rfe8 21. f3) 16... Bxd4 17. h3 (17. Rb1 c5 18. Nd2 Qa2 19. Qc4 Qxa5) 17... c5 18. Nd2 c4 (18... Rac8 19. Qc4) (18... Rfd8 19. Nf3 (19. Nc4 Nxe4) (19. Qc4 Bxf2+ 20. Kxf2 Rxd2+) 19... c4) 19. Nxc4 Nxe4 20. Be3 Bxe3 $44 {Black has compensation for the sacrificed pawn.} 21. Nxe3 Nc5 (21... Rad8 22. Rad1) (21... Nf6 22. Nc4 e4 23. Nb6 Ra7 24. Rad1) 22. Rad1 Rad8 (22... b3 23. Rd5) 23. b3 $2 f6 $1 24. Qf3 h6 (24... e4 25. Qh5) 25. Rd5 (25. Nf5 Kh7 26. Qg4 g6 27. Qxb4 gxf5 28. Qxc5) 25... Rxd5 26. Nxd5 Rb8 (26... e4 27. Qh5 f5 28. Nxb4 Rb8) 27. Rd1 $6 {An imprecision} Kh8 $6 28. h4 (28. Ne3) 28... f5 (28... Qc6 29. h5 Ne6) 29. Nb6 Ne4 $2 {An unnecessary intermediate move.} 30. Qd3 Nc3 31. Qd6 Qxd6 32. Rxd6 $2 {This loses the game.} Ne2+ (32... Nb5) 33. Kf1 Nd4 $19 34. Nc4 Ra8 35. Nxe5 Nxc2 36. Nd3 Rc8 (36... Kh7) 37. Rxa6 $2 {A mistake in a lost position.} Rc3 38. Ne5 (38. Nf4 Rxb3 39. Ra8+ Kh7 40. h5) 38... Rxb3 39. Ra8+ (39. Nc6) 39... Kh7 40. g4 (40. h5 Rb1+ 41. Ke2 Re1+ 42. Kd3 Rxe5 43. Kxc2 f4 44. Kb3 Rxh5 $13 {0-1 (35) Ward,C (2498)-Rowson,J (2545) Torquay 2002} 45. Kxb4 f3 46. gxf3 Rh1) (40. a6 Rb1+ 41. Ke2 Re1+ $13 42. Kd2 $5 Rxe5 43. Kxc2 Rb5 (43... h5 44. Kb3 Rb5 45. Rc8) 44. Kb3 $5 Rb6 45. a7 Ra6 $5 46. h5 Ra1 47. Kxb4 Rb1+ 48. Kc5 Ra1 {was played by Kasparov in blitz.} 49. Kd6 {or} Ra6+ {have been played more often.} {The alternative is} 50. Ke5 Ra5+ 51. Ke6 f4 52. f3 Ra2 53. Ke5 Ra4 54. Kf5 Ra1 55. Kxf4 Ra2 56. Ke5 Ra1 57. g4 Ra2 58. f4 Ra1 59. f5 (59. g5 hxg5 60. fxg5 g6 61. hxg6+ Kg7) 59... Ra2 60. g5 hxg5 61. h6 gxh6 62. f6) 40... Rb1+ $1 41. Kg2 Ne1+ (41... Re1) 42. Kg3 Rb3+ 43. Kf4 Nd3+ (43... fxg4 44. Kxg4 ({or} 44. Ke4 Nf3 45. Nc6 Ra3) 44... Nd3 45. f4 Ra3 46. Kf5 Nxe5 47. fxe5 $11 b3 {is worth considering:} 48. Rb8 Rxa5) 44. Kxf5 Nxe5 45. Kxe5 Rd3 46. a6 Rd1 47. a7 (47. h5 $11 {For} b3 48. Rb8 Ra1 {see the previous comment.} {After} 49. Rxb3 Rxa6) 47... Ra1 48. Kd4 g5 49. hxg5 hxg5 50. Kc4 b3 {A much better try was} 51. Kxb3 $1 Kg7 52. Kc4 Ra2 53. Kd5 Rd2+ 54. Ke4 Re2+ 55. Kd3 Ra2 56. f3 Ra3+ 57. Kd4 $11 {with equality.} {After} Ra1 58. Ke5 Ra5+ 59. Kd6 Ra6+ $17 {Black is better.} 60. Kc7 Ra3 $17 {A more precise move was} 61. Kc6 $1 Rc3+ (61... Ra1 62. Rd8) 62. Kd5 Ra3 63. Kc5 Ra6 (63... Ra1 64. Kb6 Rb1+ 65. Kc6 Rc1+ 66. Kd6 Rd1+ 67. Ke6 $17 {Black has the upper hand.} Re1+ (67... Ra1 68. Rd8 Rxa7 $44 69. Rd7+) {It was better to centralise the knight:} 68. Kf5) (63... Kh7) 64. Kc4 $19 {and Black is winning.} Ra3 65. Kb5 Ra1 66. Kb6 Rb1+ 67. Kc6 $19 {After} Rc1+ 68. Kd6 Rd1+ 69. Ke6 0-1


