1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. Be3 Bg7 7. f3 Nc6 8. Qd2 O-O 9. O-O-O d5 10. Qe1 e6 (10... dxe4 $2 11. Nxc6) (10... Nxd4 $2 11. Bxd4 e6 12. h4) 11. Kb1 $5 (11. exd5 $6 Nxd5 $1 (11... exd5 $6 12. Kb1 $14) 12. Nxd5 exd5 $132 {[%cal Yf8e8]}) (11. h4 {is the main line.}) 11... Qe7 12. Nb3 (12. Bg5 h6 (12... Nxd4 $2 {can be strongly met by} 13. e5 $1 Nc6 14. f4 $1 $16) 13. Bh4 Nxd4 14. Rxd4 (14. e5 Nf5 15. exf6 Bxf6 $15) 14... Qc5 15. Rd1 dxe4 16. Bxf6 Bxf6 17. Nxe4 Qe5 18. Nxf6+ Qxf6 19. h4 b6 20. h5 g5 21. Qe4 Rb8 22. Bd3 Rd8 {Wei Yi-Lu Shanglei, Danzhou 2015, and Black was OK.}) (12. exd5 Nxd5 13. Nxd5 exd5 14. Qd2 Re8 15. Bf2 Bd7 $132 {with equal chances.}) 12... Rd8 13. Bb5 dxe4 14. Bc5 (14. Rxd8+ Qxd8 15. fxe4 Bd7 {shouldn't be too problematic for Black either.}) 14... Qc7 15. Rxd8+ Qxd8 ({In an earlier game Black tried} 15... Nxd8 $1 16. Nxe4 Nxe4 17. Qxe4 Bd7 $11 {Ivanchuk-Georgiev, Tilburg 1993, and in my opinion Black doesn't face any problems.}) 16. Nxe4 Nxe4 17. Qxe4 e5 18. g4 Be6 19. Bc4 Bxc4 20. Qxc4 Qf6 21. Qe4 Rd8 22. Be3 Rd6 (22... b6 {followed by 23...e6 and 24...d5, leads to equality.}) 23. a3 Qd8 24. Ka2 Qc8 25. g5 Qh3 26. Qg4 Qxg4 27. fxg4 b6 28. Nd2 Kf8 29. Ne4 Rd8 30. h4 Ke7 31. h5 Nd4 32. c3 Ne6 33. Kb3 Nc7 34. a4 Nd5 35. Bc1 Ke6 36. Rf1 Rd7 37. Kc2 gxh5 38. gxh5 f5 39. gxf6 Nxf6 40. Ng5+ Ke7 41. Rf5 Nxh5 42. Nxh7 Nf6 43. Rxe5+ Kd6 44. Nxf6 Bxf6 45. Rh5 Be5 46. Kb3 Re7 47. Bg5 Rg7 48. Bh6 Rf7 49. Kc4 Rf2 50. b4 Rg2 51. Bf8+ Ke6 52. Rh3 Rc2 53. Re3 Kf5 54. Rd3 Ke6 55. Re3 Kf5 56. Rh3 Ke6 57. Rf3 a6 58. Re3 Kf5 59. Rd3 Ke6 60. Re3 Kf5 61. b5 axb5+ 62. axb5 Rd2 63. Rh3 Rd8 64. Bb4 Ke6 65. Rh6+ Bf6 66. Rh7 Rd7 67. Rh2 Be5 68. Rh6+ Bf6 69. Rh2 Be5 70. Re2 Rh7 71. Kb3 Rh3 72. Re1 Kd5 73. Rd1+ Ke6 74. Re1 Kd5 75. Rg1 Bf6 $2 ({A huge blunder, allowing the rook to pick up the pawn on b6. After} 75... Ke6 $11 {there is no chance to break through.}) 76. Rd1+ Ke4 77. Rd6 Be5 78. Rxb6 Kd3 79. Re6 Bf4 80. Re7 Rh1 81. Rd7+ Ke4 82. Kc4 Rh6 83. Bc5 Ke5 84. Re7+ Kf6 85. Re8 Rh1 86. Rf8+ Kg5 87. b6 Rh7 88. Kb5 Be5 89. Bd4 Bd6 90. Rf1 Bf4 91. Ka6 Rh2 92. Rxf4 Ra2+ 93. Kb7 Kxf4 94. Kc7 Re2 95. b7 Re7+ 96. Kb6 Re8 97. Ka7 Re7 98. Ka8 1-0


