1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Nf3 b6 5. e3 Ne4 6. Qc2 Bb7 7. Bd3 f5 8. O-O Bxc3 9. bxc3 O-O 10. Nd2 Qh4 11. f3 Nxd2 12. Bxd2 d6 13. Rae1 Nd7 14. e4 f4 15. Qa4 Qe7 16. g3 {A new attempt in a well-known variation that soon leads to a curious and rarely seen pawn formation.} g5 17. h4 gxh4 18. gxf4 Kh8 19. Kf2 h3 20. Ke2 Rg8 21. Rh1 Rg3 22. Be3 Nf6 23. Bf2 $6 {This attempt to drive out the black rook backfires.} ({Komodo recommends} 23. d5 {with an equal position.}) 23... Nh5 $1 24. Bxg3 Nxg3+ 25. Ke3 Qh4 $1 {Black refrains from winning back the exchange immediately and prefers to increase the pressure. The main threat is ...Rf8.} 26. Qb5 {Hopes to transfer the queen to the kingside, but...} e5 $1 {Black prevents such ideas and now has a winning position.} 27. Qd7 ({After} 27. dxe5 Rf8 {Black is winning, e.g.} 28. Be2 Qxf4+ 29. Kd3 Nxe2 30. Rxe2 Qxf3+) 27... Qxf4+ 28. Kf2 Qd2+ $1 29. Be2 ({After} 29. Kxg3 Rg8+ {White has to give his queen to avoid mate.}) 29... Nxe4+ 30. fxe4 Rf8+ 31. Kg3 Bc8 $1 0-1


