1. c4 Nf6 2. Nc3 e5 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. g3 d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. Bg2 Nb6 7. O-O Be7 8. a3 O-O 9. b4 Be6 10. d3 a5 11. b5 Nd4 12. Bb2 Nxf3+ {A very rare move, which seems to be not bad at all, at least in view of this game.} (12... Nb3 13. Rb1 f6 {Azmaiparashvili,Z (2540)-Romanishin,O (2570)/Tallinn 1988/EXT 2000/ (0-1, 44)}) (12... Bb3 13. Qc1 Be6 14. Rb1 {Marin,M (2557)-Stefansson,H (2557)/Istanbul 2000/EXT 2001/[Marin,M] (1-0, 58)}) 13. Bxf3 Rb8 14. Qc2 Qd7 15. Rfc1 Bd6 16. Rab1 f5 17. Na4 Nxa4 18. Qxa4 b6 19. Rc6 Qf7 {Despite the apparent positional concessions, Black's queenside position is very hard to crack. At the same time, his attack on the other wing is ready to start.} 20. Rf1 Kh8 21. Bg2 Rbe8 22. Qc2 Bd7 {Allowing the opening of the queenside.} (22... f4 $5) 23. Rxc7 Bxc7 24. Qxc7 Bxb5 25. Qxb6 $44 Qb3 26. Ba1 a4 27. Qc5 e4 28. Rc1 Rf7 29. g4 $5 Bd7 30. gxf5 exd3 31. Bd5 dxe2 32. Bxb3 e1=Q+ 33. Rxe1 Rxe1+ 34. Kg2 axb3 35. f6 Rxa1 36. Qd5 Be8 37. Qe4 gxf6 38. Qxe8+ Kg7 39. Qb8 Rxa3 40. Qg3+ Kh8 41. Qb8+ Kg7 42. Qg3+ Kh8 1/2-1/2


