1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. Qe2 Be7 6. c3 b5 7. Bb3 O-O 8. d3 d6 9. Nbd2 h6 10. Nf1 Re8 11. Ng3 Bf8 12. O-O Na5 13. Bc2 c5 14. h3 Nc6 15. Nh2 Ra7 16. Ng4 Nxg4 17. hxg4 Be7 18. Nf5 Bg5 19. Bxg5 hxg5 20. g3 g6 21. Ne3 Be6 22. Bb3 Qc8 23. Kg2 Bxb3 24. axb3 Qe6 25. Rh1 Kg7 26. Rh3 Raa8 27. Nd5 Ra7 28. Qe3 Ne7 29. Qxg5 Nxd5 30. Rah1 Rg8 31. exd5 Qxd5+ 32. Kg1 Raa8 33. Qe7 Rh8 {[%tqu "En","White's attack needs extra power. How can you fuel it up?","Try to gain control over the f6-square.","The pawn advancement is the strongest move in this position.","g4g5","The pawn thrust adds decisive momentum to White's attack.",5]} 34. g5 $1 {[%csl Rf6][%cal Ge7f6,Gg5f6,Gf6h8,Gh1h8] Excellent and very efficient move, creating a decisive threat 35.f6+.} Qe6 (34... Rxh3 {fails to} 35. Qf6+ Kf8 36. Rxh3 Ke8 37. c4 $1 Qb7 (37... Qe6 38. Qxe6+ fxe6 39. Rh8+) (37... Qc6 38. Rh8+ Kd7 39. Qxf7#) 38. Qxd6 {, and Black is defenseless against the threat 39.h8#.}) {[%tqu "En","How can White finish his attack?","Try to deflect the black king from protecting the h8-rook.","Use your queen for the final blow.","e7f6","This simple and nice move crowns White's attack.",4]} 35. Qf6+ $1 {[%csl Rh8][%cal Gh1h8]} (35. Qf6+ {, and Black resigned, since he loses the rook:} Qxf6 36. gxf6+ Kxf6 37. Rxh8) 1-0


