1. e4 c5 2. c3 Nf6 3. e5 Nd5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Bc4 Nb6 6. Bb3 c4 7. Bc2 d5 8. exd6 e5 9. O-O Be6 10. a4 $5 {Recommended by Dave Smerdon in his notes to M. Adams - R.Wojtaszek, Biel 2015 (1/2 - 1/2 in 41).} Bxd6 {Dave covered 10... Qxd6 and 10...a5.} (10... a6 {looks logical, preventing White's pawn from reaching a6, but White can open the position to his advantage after} 11. a5 Nd7 12. d4 cxd3 13. Qxd3 Nc5 14. Qe2 Bxd6 {P.Roberson - A.Bitalzadeh, chess.com INT 2017 (0-1 in 52) and now} 15. Nbd2 h6 16. Nc4 $16 {is excellent for White.}) 11. a5 Nd7 12. d4 (12. a6 $5 bxa6 {seems to be a useful inclusion:} 13. Be4 (13. Rxa6 Qc8 $11 {1/2-1/2 (38) Roberson,P (2401)-Lalic,B (2443) London 2016}) (13. d4 $5) 13... Rc8 14. d4 exd4 15. Bxc6 Rxc6 16. Nxd4 Rb6 17. Nxe6 fxe6 18. Qh5+ g6 19. Qh3 $16) 12... cxd3 13. Qxd3 Be7 14. a6 b6 (14... bxa6 15. Qxa6 $16 {is also excellent for White.}) 15. Re1 $6 {According to the engines this gives up some of White's advantage, but I find this assessment hard to believe.} (15. Rd1 Rc8 16. Na3 f5 17. Nb5 O-O 18. Qe2 $16 {was H.Stevic - B.Lalic, Mali Losinj 2017  (1-0 in 48).}) 15... Rc8 16. Na3 Bxa3 17. Rxa3 f6 (17... h6 {is the move the engines want to play, though it's hard to see how Black will bring his king to safety. To me this position just looks horrible for Black even though Stockfish says its just a white edge.}) 18. Be3 $6 (18. Nd4 $1 $16 {was an important opportunity. If Black takes on d4 the a3-rook can come into play along the third rank, and after} Nc5 19. Qg3 exd4 20. Qxg7 Rf8 21. b4 $16 {the complications favour White.}) 18... Kf7 (18... Qc7 {followed by ...Ne7 was a better defence.}) 19. Raa1 Qc7 20. Rad1 $2 {Allowing an equalising shot.} (20. Qe2 $14 {would retain an excellent position.}) 20... Nb4 $1 21. Qe2 (21. cxb4 Qxc2 $15 {is no improvement.}) 21... Nxc2 22. Qxc2 Nb8 $11 {Important attacking pieces have been exchanged and White needs to concern himself with defence of his a6-pawn. The game was drawn after further adventures.} 23. Qa4 Rhd8 24. h3 Qc4 25. Qa3 Qb3 26. Qxb3 Bxb3 27. Rxd8 Rxd8 28. Nd2 Be6 29. Ra1 Bc8 30. b4 Bxa6 31. c4 Rd7 32. b5 Bc8 33. c5 bxc5 34. Ne4 Rc7 35. Bxc5 Ke6 36. Bxa7 Nd7 37. g4 Bb7 38. Ng3 g6 39. Re1 1/2-1/2


